WEBVTT

1
00:00:48.799 --> 00:00:50.176
ROGERS: On your left.

2
00:01:00.895 --> 00:01:02.104
On your left.

3
00:01:02.188 --> 00:01:04.232
MAN: Uh-huh. On my left. Got it.

4
00:01:09.987 --> 00:01:11.364
Don't say it. Don't you say it.

5
00:01:11.447 --> 00:01:12.990
- On your left.
- Come on!

6
00:01:13.991 --> 00:01:15.826
(PANTING) Oh!

7
00:01:15.910 --> 00:01:18.204
(GROANING)

8
00:01:21.832 --> 00:01:23.417
Need a medic?

9
00:01:23.501 --> 00:01:24.543
(LAUGHS)

10
00:01:26.128 --> 00:01:27.838
I need a new set of lungs.

11
00:01:27.922 --> 00:01:31.259
Dude. you just ran.
like. 13 miles in 30 minutes.

12
00:01:31.342 --> 00:01:32.343
I guess I got a late start.

13
00:01:32.593 --> 00:01:35.054
(CHUCKLES) Really? You should
be ashamed of yourself.

14
00:01:35.304 --> 00:01:37.765
You should take another lap.

15
00:01:37.974 --> 00:01:40.017
Did you just take it?
I assume you just took it.

16
00:01:40.476 --> 00:01:41.769
What unit you with?

17
00:01:41.978 --> 00:01:43.312
58th Pararescue.

18
00:01:43.521 --> 00:01:45.022
But now I'm working down at the VA.

19
00:01:45.773 --> 00:01:47.358
- Sam Wilson.
- Steve Rogers.

20
00:01:47.525 --> 00:01:49.694
I kind of put that together. (PANTING)

21
00:01:50.820 --> 00:01:53.322
Must have freaked you out. coming
home after the whole defrosting thing.

22
00:01:53.447 --> 00:01:55.866
(SIGHS) It takes some getting used to.

23
00:01:56.033 --> 00:01:57.451
It's good to meet you. Sam.

24
00:01:57.868 --> 00:01:58.869
It's your bed. right?

25
00:02:00.121 --> 00:02:01.038
What's that?

26
00:02:01.205 --> 00:02:02.623
Your bed. it's too soft.

27
00:02:02.873 --> 00:02:04.458
When I was over there.
I'd sleep on the ground.

28
00:02:04.667 --> 00:02:06.544
use rock for pillows. like a caveman.

29
00:02:06.877 --> 00:02:09.880
Now I'm home. lying in my bed.
and it's like...

30
00:02:10.006 --> 00:02:11.257
Lying on a marshmallow.

31
00:02:11.340 --> 00:02:13.009
Feel like I'm gonna sink
right to the floor.

32
00:02:14.385 --> 00:02:15.636
How long?

33
00:02:15.720 --> 00:02:17.013
Two tours.

34
00:02:18.055 --> 00:02:19.473
You must miss the good old days. huh?

35
00:02:20.433 --> 00:02:22.893
Well. things aren't so bad.

36
00:02:23.102 --> 00:02:25.479
Food's a lot better.
We used to boil everything.

37
00:02:25.563 --> 00:02:26.856
No polio is good.

38
00:02:26.939 --> 00:02:28.190
Internet. so helpful.

39
00:02:28.399 --> 00:02:29.775
I've been reading that a lot.
trying to catch up.

40
00:02:31.944 --> 00:02:35.906
Marvin Gaye. 1972.
<i>Trouble Man</i> soundtrack.

41
00:02:36.115 --> 00:02:38.576
Everything you missed
jammed into one album.

42
00:02:38.743 --> 00:02:40.703
I'll put it on the list.

43
00:02:44.749 --> 00:02:46.625
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

44
00:02:48.377 --> 00:02:51.047
All right. Sam. duty calls.
Thanks for the run.

45
00:02:51.297 --> 00:02:52.590
If that's what you want to call running.

46
00:02:52.798 --> 00:02:53.799
Oh. that's how it is?

47
00:02:53.883 --> 00:02:54.925
- Oh. that's how it is.
- Okay. (LAUGHS)

48
00:02:56.594 --> 00:02:58.929
Any time you want to stop by the VA.
make me look awesome

49
00:02:59.096 --> 00:03:02.433
in front of the girl at the front desk.
just let me know.

50
00:03:02.600 --> 00:03:04.226
- I'll keep it in mind.
- Yeah.

51
00:03:08.230 --> 00:03:09.774
Hey. fellas.

52
00:03:09.982 --> 00:03:11.734
Either one of you
know where the Smithsonian is?

53
00:03:11.942 --> 00:03:13.152
I'm here to pick up a fossil.

54
00:03:13.611 --> 00:03:14.612
ROGERS: That's hilarious.

55
00:03:18.074 --> 00:03:19.075
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

56
00:03:19.158 --> 00:03:20.618
- How you doing?
- Hey.

57
00:03:22.078 --> 00:03:23.371
Can't run everywhere.

58
00:03:23.454 --> 00:03:24.455
No. you can't.

59
00:03:26.207 --> 00:03:27.708
(TYRES SCREECHING)

60
00:03:32.296 --> 00:03:34.423
Target is a mobile
satellite launch platform.

61
00:03:34.507 --> 00:03:35.633
the <i>Lemurian Star.</i>

62
00:03:35.966 --> 00:03:38.094
They were sending up their last payload
when pirates took them.

63
00:03:38.719 --> 00:03:40.012
93 minutes ago.

64
00:03:40.221 --> 00:03:41.972
- Any demands?
- Billion and a half.

65
00:03:42.139 --> 00:03:43.808
- ROGERS: Why so steep?
- Because it's S.H.I.E.L.D.'s.

66
00:03:46.310 --> 00:03:47.978
So it's not off-course. It's trespassing.

67
00:03:48.145 --> 00:03:49.647
I'm sure they have a good reason.

68
00:03:49.814 --> 00:03:51.524
You know. I'm getting a little
tired of being Fury's janitor.

69
00:03:51.732 --> 00:03:53.567
Relax. It's not that complicated.

70
00:03:53.776 --> 00:03:54.860
How many pirates?

71
00:03:54.944 --> 00:03:57.488
25. Top mercs led by this guy.

72
00:03:58.280 --> 00:04:01.742
Georges Batroc.
Ex-DGSE. Action Division.

73
00:04:01.951 --> 00:04:03.828
He's at the top of Interpol's Red Notice.

74
00:04:04.495 --> 00:04:07.665
Before the French demobilised him.
he had 36 kill missions.

75
00:04:07.915 --> 00:04:09.500
This guy's got a rep
for maximum casualties.

76
00:04:09.708 --> 00:04:10.960
Hostages?

77
00:04:11.043 --> 00:04:13.921
Oh. mostly techs. One officer.
Jasper Sitwell.

78
00:04:14.588 --> 00:04:15.840
They're in the galley.

79
00:04:16.006 --> 00:04:17.466
What's Sitwell doing on a launch ship?

80
00:04:17.675 --> 00:04:19.510
All right. I'm gonna
sweep the deck and find Batroc.

81
00:04:19.718 --> 00:04:21.178
Nat. you kill the engines
and wait for instructions.

82
00:04:21.679 --> 00:04:24.181
Rumlow. you sweep aft.
find the hostages.

83
00:04:24.348 --> 00:04:26.142
get them to the life-pods. get them out.
Let's move.

84
00:04:26.225 --> 00:04:27.351
S.T.R.I.K.E.. you heard the Cap.
Gear up.

85
00:04:41.490 --> 00:04:42.575
Secure channel seven.

86
00:04:42.658 --> 00:04:43.784
Seven secure.

87
00:04:43.868 --> 00:04:45.411
Did you do anything fun
Saturday night?

88
00:04:45.661 --> 00:04:49.039
Well. all the guys
from my barbershop quartet are dead.

89
00:04:49.206 --> 00:04:50.749
so. no. not really.

90
00:04:50.833 --> 00:04:53.043
MALE PILOT ON RADIO:
<i>Coming up on the drop zone. Cap.</i>

91
00:04:53.252 --> 00:04:56.255
You know. if you ask Kristen out.
from Statistics. she'd probably say yes.

92
00:04:57.173 --> 00:04:58.132
That's why I don't ask.

93
00:05:00.050 --> 00:05:01.635
Too shy. or too scared?

94
00:05:02.428 --> 00:05:03.762
Too busy!

95
00:05:05.222 --> 00:05:06.807
Was he wearing a parachute?

96
00:05:07.016 --> 00:05:08.058
No.

97
00:05:08.684 --> 00:05:09.727
No. he wasn't.

98
00:05:09.727 --> 00:05:39.727
<b>Subtitle 
 www.movieddl.me</b>

99
00:06:10.746 --> 00:06:11.956
Ahh!

100
00:06:18.546 --> 00:06:19.630
Ahh!

101
00:06:19.713 --> 00:06:20.965
(SPLASHES)

102
00:06:22.466 --> 00:06:23.634
(BOTH GRUNTING)

103
00:06:24.176 --> 00:06:25.177
Hey!

104
00:06:31.642 --> 00:06:32.935
(SCREAMS)

105
00:06:43.988 --> 00:06:45.155
(GRUNTING)

106
00:07:02.965 --> 00:07:03.966
- (COCKS GUN)
- (SPEAKS FRENCH)

107
00:07:04.049 --> 00:07:05.050
Don't move.

108
00:07:09.221 --> 00:07:10.222
Thanks.

109
00:07:10.472 --> 00:07:12.474
Yeah. You seemed pretty
helpless without me.

110
00:07:17.146 --> 00:07:18.814
What about the nurse that
lives across the hall from you?

111
00:07:18.897 --> 00:07:19.940
She seems kind of nice.

112
00:07:20.024 --> 00:07:21.650
Secure the engine room.
then find me a date.

113
00:07:21.859 --> 00:07:23.444
I'm multi-tasking.

114
00:07:23.527 --> 00:07:24.612
(FRENCH PIRATE
SPEAKING FRENCH)

115
00:07:24.820 --> 00:07:25.863
I told Batroc...

116
00:07:26.238 --> 00:07:27.489
If we want to make S.H.I.E.L.D. pay us...

117
00:07:27.740 --> 00:07:29.783
...start sending them bodies now!

118
00:07:31.660 --> 00:07:33.704
I have a bullet for someone...

119
00:07:34.538 --> 00:07:36.040
You want a bullet in your head?

120
00:07:36.332 --> 00:07:37.875
Move that foot - you want
a bullet in the head...?

121
00:07:38.542 --> 00:07:39.877
Huh?

122
00:07:46.216 --> 00:07:47.551
(BATROC SPEAKING FRENCH)

123
00:07:47.885 --> 00:07:49.720
I don't like waiting.

124
00:07:50.846 --> 00:07:52.014
Call Durand.

125
00:07:52.681 --> 00:07:55.309
I want this ship ready to move
when the ransom comes.

126
00:07:55.392 --> 00:07:56.977
(RADIO PIRATE SPEAKING FRENCH)

127
00:08:03.067 --> 00:08:04.068
Start the engines.

128
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:05.486
Okay.

129
00:08:06.779 --> 00:08:07.821
Hey. sailor.

130
00:08:09.782 --> 00:08:10.908
(SCREAMS)

131
00:08:12.743 --> 00:08:13.786
(CHOKING)

132
00:08:25.756 --> 00:08:27.383
(PIRATE SPEAKING FRENCH)

133
00:08:27.633 --> 00:08:28.634
Shut up.

134
00:08:29.968 --> 00:08:32.262
You want to be a hero? Is that it?

135
00:08:38.769 --> 00:08:40.979
All right. I've waited long enough...

136
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:45.567
Hey!

137
00:08:45.651 --> 00:08:46.652
Find Batroc...

138
00:08:46.735 --> 00:08:47.736
If I don't hear anything in two minutes...

139
00:08:47.903 --> 00:08:49.071
...I start killing them!

140
00:08:49.279 --> 00:08:50.280
I'll find him.

141
00:08:59.331 --> 00:09:00.249
Two minutes.

142
00:09:31.655 --> 00:09:33.991
Radio silence
from S.H.I.E.L.D.. Batroc...

143
00:09:38.370 --> 00:09:39.413
Targets acquired.

144
00:09:40.122 --> 00:09:41.165
S.T.R.I.K.E. in position.

145
00:09:42.291 --> 00:09:43.333
Natasha. what's your status?

146
00:09:46.003 --> 00:09:47.004
<i>Status. Natasha.</i>

147
00:09:47.171 --> 00:09:48.172
Hang on!

148
00:09:52.509 --> 00:09:53.677
(GROANING)

149
00:10:04.229 --> 00:10:05.355
Engine room secure.

150
00:10:12.905 --> 00:10:13.989
(PIRATE SPEAKING FRENCH)

151
00:10:14.072 --> 00:10:15.073
Time is up.

152
00:10:16.492 --> 00:10:18.076
Who dies first...?

153
00:10:19.536 --> 00:10:20.537
You!

154
00:10:20.621 --> 00:10:21.622
Get that one.

155
00:10:24.208 --> 00:10:25.209
On my mark.

156
00:10:26.668 --> 00:10:28.003
<i>Three...</i>

157
00:10:28.212 --> 00:10:29.505
<i>Two... One.</i>

158
00:10:29.713 --> 00:10:31.131
- (GUNFIRE)
- (PIRATES GASP)

159
00:10:35.844 --> 00:10:38.889
I told you.
S.H.I.E.L.D. doesn't negotiate.

160
00:10:39.306 --> 00:10:40.891
(RADIO PIRATE SPEAKING FRENCH)

161
00:10:42.559 --> 00:10:44.019
The line just went dead.

162
00:10:44.311 --> 00:10:45.729
I've lost contact with them...

163
00:10:47.856 --> 00:10:49.066
Ahh!

164
00:10:59.284 --> 00:11:01.411
Hostages en route to extraction.

165
00:11:02.287 --> 00:11:04.706
<i>Romanoff missed
the rendezvous point. Cap.</i>

166
00:11:05.290 --> 00:11:07.251
<i>Hostiles are still in play.</i>

167
00:11:07.417 --> 00:11:09.753
(PANTING)
Natasha. Batroc's on the move.

168
00:11:09.962 --> 00:11:12.005
Circle back to Rumlow
and protect the hostages.

169
00:11:12.923 --> 00:11:14.049
Natasha.

170
00:11:15.676 --> 00:11:16.885
(BOTH GRUNTING)

171
00:11:49.126 --> 00:11:50.294
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

172
00:11:50.586 --> 00:11:52.212
I thought you were
more than just a shield...

173
00:12:06.476 --> 00:12:07.978
Let's see.

174
00:12:32.586 --> 00:12:33.629
(PANTING)

175
00:12:33.754 --> 00:12:35.297
ROMANOFF:Well. this is awkward.

176
00:12:38.717 --> 00:12:39.927
What are you doing?

177
00:12:40.093 --> 00:12:41.303
Backing up the hard drive.

178
00:12:41.386 --> 00:12:42.804
It's a good habit to get into.

179
00:12:43.305 --> 00:12:44.348
Rumlow needed your help.

180
00:12:44.473 --> 00:12:45.766
What the hell are you doing here?

181
00:12:49.353 --> 00:12:50.562
You're saving S.H.I.E.L.D. intel.

182
00:12:50.687 --> 00:12:51.980
Whatever I can get my hands on.

183
00:12:52.147 --> 00:12:53.523
Our mission is to rescue hostages.

184
00:12:53.649 --> 00:12:55.484
No. that's your mission.

185
00:12:57.319 --> 00:12:58.278
and you've done it beautifully.

186
00:12:59.488 --> 00:13:01.239
You just jeopardised
this whole operation.

187
00:13:01.448 --> 00:13:02.783
I think that's overstating things.

188
00:13:15.003 --> 00:13:16.338
(BOTH GROANING)

189
00:13:17.881 --> 00:13:19.383
(BOTH PANTING)

190
00:13:20.801 --> 00:13:21.927
Okay.

191
00:13:22.636 --> 00:13:23.845
That one's on me.

192
00:13:24.888 --> 00:13:26.223
You're damn right.

193
00:13:29.518 --> 00:13:30.727
(SIGHS)

194
00:13:55.127 --> 00:13:57.170
ROGERS: You just can't stop yourself
from lying. can you?

195
00:13:57.254 --> 00:13:58.296
FURY: I didn't lie.

196
00:13:58.380 --> 00:13:59.715
Agent Romanoff
had a different mission than yours.

197
00:13:59.923 --> 00:14:01.675
Which you didn't feel obliged to share.

198
00:14:01.883 --> 00:14:03.427
I'm not obliged to do anything.

199
00:14:03.593 --> 00:14:05.012
Those hostages could have died. Nick.

200
00:14:05.220 --> 00:14:08.807
I sent the greatest soldier in history
to make sure that didn't happen.

201
00:14:09.016 --> 00:14:11.101
Soldiers trust each other.
That's what makes it an army.

202
00:14:11.309 --> 00:14:12.936
Not a bunch of guys
running around shooting guns.

203
00:14:13.103 --> 00:14:16.314
Last time I trusted someone.
I lost an eye.

204
00:14:17.315 --> 00:14:20.736
Look. I didn't want you doing
anything you weren't comfortable with.

205
00:14:20.861 --> 00:14:22.988
Agent Romanoff is comfortable
with everything.

206
00:14:23.196 --> 00:14:24.364
I can't lead a mission

207
00:14:24.573 --> 00:14:26.283
when the people I'm leading
have missions of their own.

208
00:14:26.491 --> 00:14:29.119
It's called compartmentalisation.

209
00:14:29.327 --> 00:14:31.997
Nobody spills the secrets.
because nobody knows them all.

210
00:14:32.956 --> 00:14:33.915
Except you.

211
00:14:37.627 --> 00:14:39.171
You're wrong about me.

212
00:14:40.005 --> 00:14:41.256
I do share.

213
00:14:42.424 --> 00:14:44.009
I'm nice like that.

214
00:14:45.927 --> 00:14:46.970
Insight bay.

215
00:14:47.054 --> 00:14:48.138
S.H.I.E.L.D. COMPUTER:
<i>Captain Rogers does not have</i>

216
00:14:48.346 --> 00:14:49.514
<i>clearance for Project Insight.</i>

217
00:14:49.723 --> 00:14:52.184
Director override. Fury. Nicholas J.

218
00:14:52.309 --> 00:14:53.894
- <i>Confirmed.</i>
- (DOOR CLOSES)

219
00:14:56.480 --> 00:14:58.315
You know. they used to play music.

220
00:14:58.982 --> 00:14:59.983
Yeah.

221
00:15:00.150 --> 00:15:03.737
My grandfather operated one
of these things for 40 years.

222
00:15:03.945 --> 00:15:06.239
Granddad worked in a nice building.

223
00:15:06.448 --> 00:15:07.657
Got good tips.

224
00:15:08.241 --> 00:15:12.329
He'd walk home every night.
a roll of ones stuffed in his lunch bag.

225
00:15:12.537 --> 00:15:13.830
He'd say. "Hi."

226
00:15:14.081 --> 00:15:15.916
People would say. "Hi" back.

227
00:15:16.666 --> 00:15:19.127
Time went on.
the neighbourhood got rougher.

228
00:15:19.211 --> 00:15:20.212
He'd say. "Hi."

229
00:15:20.879 --> 00:15:22.756
They'd say. "Keep on steppin'."

230
00:15:22.964 --> 00:15:25.050
Granddad got to gripping that
lunch bag a little tighter.

231
00:15:26.009 --> 00:15:27.010
Did he ever get mugged?

232
00:15:27.344 --> 00:15:28.553
(LAUGHS)

233
00:15:29.137 --> 00:15:31.973
Every week some punk would say.
"What's in the bag?"

234
00:15:32.182 --> 00:15:33.850
What would he do?

235
00:15:34.059 --> 00:15:35.185
He'd show them.

236
00:15:35.852 --> 00:15:39.231
Bunch of crumpled ones.
and a loaded .22 Magnum.

237
00:15:43.401 --> 00:15:45.070
Yeah. Granddad loved people.

238
00:15:46.029 --> 00:15:48.323
But he didn't trust them very much.

239
00:15:54.121 --> 00:15:55.831
Yeah. I know.

240
00:15:56.039 --> 00:15:58.375
They're a little bit bigger than a .22.

241
00:16:32.701 --> 00:16:35.120
FURY: This is Project Insight.

242
00:16:35.328 --> 00:16:37.497
Three next-generation helicarriers

243
00:16:37.706 --> 00:16:40.375
synced to a network
of targeting satellites.

244
00:16:40.584 --> 00:16:42.335
Launched from the <i>Lemurian Star.</i>

245
00:16:42.544 --> 00:16:45.505
Once we get them in the air.
they never need to come down.

246
00:16:45.755 --> 00:16:50.594
Continuous sub-orbital flight.
courtesy of our new repulsor engines.

247
00:16:50.802 --> 00:16:52.095
Stark?

248
00:16:52.179 --> 00:16:53.388
He had a few suggestions

249
00:16:53.471 --> 00:16:55.807
once he got an up-close look
at our old turbines.

250
00:16:56.683 --> 00:16:59.102
These new long-range precision guns

251
00:16:59.269 --> 00:17:01.730
can eliminate 1.000 hostiles a minute.

252
00:17:01.938 --> 00:17:06.109
The satellites can read a terrorist's DNA
before he steps outside his spider hole.

253
00:17:06.610 --> 00:17:09.404
We're gonna neutralise a lot of threats
before they even happen.

254
00:17:09.613 --> 00:17:11.489
Thought the punishment
usually came after the crime.

255
00:17:11.698 --> 00:17:13.116
We can't afford to wait that long.

256
00:17:13.283 --> 00:17:14.784
Who's "we"?

257
00:17:14.993 --> 00:17:17.245
After New York. I convinced
the World Security Council

258
00:17:17.454 --> 00:17:19.706
we needed a quantum surge
in threat analysis.

259
00:17:20.582 --> 00:17:22.792
For once. we're way ahead of the curve.

260
00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:26.463
By holding a gun to everyone on Earth
and calling it protection.

261
00:17:28.089 --> 00:17:30.133
You know. I read those SSR files.

262
00:17:30.926 --> 00:17:32.010
"Greatest Generation"?

263
00:17:32.761 --> 00:17:34.387
You guys did some nasty stuff.

264
00:17:34.596 --> 00:17:36.139
Yeah. we compromised.

265
00:17:36.640 --> 00:17:38.475
Sometimes in ways that
made us not sleep so well.

266
00:17:38.975 --> 00:17:41.228
But we did it
so that people could be free.

267
00:17:41.436 --> 00:17:43.647
This isn't freedom. This is fear.

268
00:17:43.813 --> 00:17:47.192
S.H.I.E.L.D. takes the world as it is.
not as we'd like it to be.

269
00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:51.363
And it's getting damn near past time
for you to get with that programme. Cap.

270
00:17:52.364 --> 00:17:54.199
Don't hold your breath.

271
00:18:12.884 --> 00:18:14.844
WOMAN ON PA:
<i>Welcome to the Smithsonian.</i>

272
00:18:15.011 --> 00:18:18.515
<i>Visitor information booths are
available on the second level.</i>

273
00:18:27.565 --> 00:18:29.693
NARRATOR: <i>A symbol to the nation.</i>

274
00:18:30.860 --> 00:18:32.654
<i>A hero to the world.</i>

275
00:18:34.030 --> 00:18:39.869
<i>The story of Captain America
is one of honour. bravery and sacrifice.</i>

276
00:18:44.541 --> 00:18:47.335
<i>Denied enlistment due to poor health.</i>

277
00:18:47.544 --> 00:18:49.754
<i>Steven Rogers was chosen
for a programme</i>

278
00:18:49.963 --> 00:18:53.091
<i>unique in the annals
of American warfare.</i>

279
00:18:54.092 --> 00:18:59.055
<i>One that would transform him
into the world's first Super-Soldier.</i>

280
00:19:05.729 --> 00:19:06.730
WAR FOOTAGE NARRATOR:
<i>In this rare footage.</i>

281
00:19:06.896 --> 00:19:09.232
<i>everyone's favourite war hero.
Captain America...</i>

282
00:19:09.399 --> 00:19:10.900
NARRATOR: <i>Battle tested.</i>

283
00:19:11.067 --> 00:19:12.068
<i>Captain America</i>

284
00:19:12.444 --> 00:19:15.572
<i>and his Howling Commandos
quickly earned their stripes.</i>

285
00:19:15.739 --> 00:19:16.781
<i>Their mission:</i>

286
00:19:17.157 --> 00:19:20.785
<i>taking down HYDRA.
the Nazi rogue science division.</i>

287
00:19:24.122 --> 00:19:26.124
<i>Best friends since childhood.</i>

288
00:19:27.083 --> 00:19:30.420
<i>Bucky Barnes and Steven Rogers
were inseparable</i>

289
00:19:30.587 --> 00:19:32.464
<i>on both schoolyard and battlefield.</i>

290
00:19:33.882 --> 00:19:37.927
<i>Barnes is the only Howling
Commando to give his life</i>

291
00:19:38.094 --> 00:19:40.638
<i>in service of his country.</i>

292
00:19:45.727 --> 00:19:47.312
PEGGY ON VIDEO:
<i>That was a difficult winter.</i>

293
00:19:47.520 --> 00:19:50.982
<i>A blizzard had trapped half
our battalion behind the German line.</i>

294
00:19:51.775 --> 00:19:54.819
<i>Steve. Captain Rogers.</i>

295
00:19:55.028 --> 00:19:57.655
<i>he fought his way
through a HYDRA blockade</i>

296
00:19:57.864 --> 00:20:00.408
<i>that had pinned our allies
down for months.</i>

297
00:20:02.369 --> 00:20:03.787
<i>He saved over 1.000 men.</i>

298
00:20:04.788 --> 00:20:06.373
<i>Including the man who would...</i>

299
00:20:07.665 --> 00:20:10.627
<i>Who would become my husband.
as it turned out.</i>

300
00:20:11.503 --> 00:20:14.297
<i>Even after he died.
Steve was still changing my life.</i>

301
00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:18.802
You should be
proud of yourself. Peggy.

302
00:20:24.849 --> 00:20:26.184
Mmm.

303
00:20:27.185 --> 00:20:29.312
I have lived a life.

304
00:20:31.231 --> 00:20:34.442
My only regret is that
you didn't get to live yours.

305
00:20:37.654 --> 00:20:38.696
What is it?

306
00:20:41.658 --> 00:20:44.911
For as long as I can remember.
I just wanted to do what was right.

307
00:20:46.371 --> 00:20:48.665
I guess I'm not quite sure
what that is any more.

308
00:20:51.543 --> 00:20:55.922
And I thought I could
throw myself back in and follow orders.

309
00:20:56.005 --> 00:20:57.465
Serve.

310
00:21:00.635 --> 00:21:02.720
It's just not the same.

311
00:21:03.054 --> 00:21:04.722
(LAUGHS) You're always so dramatic.

312
00:21:07.976 --> 00:21:11.563
Look. you saved the world.

313
00:21:14.023 --> 00:21:17.861
We rather mucked it up.

314
00:21:18.236 --> 00:21:19.529
You didn't.

315
00:21:20.071 --> 00:21:23.783
Knowing that you helped found
S.H.I.E.L.D. is half the reason I stay.

316
00:21:24.659 --> 00:21:25.660
Hey.

317
00:21:28.538 --> 00:21:32.750
The world has changed.
and none of us can go back.

318
00:21:33.960 --> 00:21:36.129
All we can do is our best.

319
00:21:36.337 --> 00:21:40.550
And sometimes the best that
we can do is to start over.

320
00:21:40.675 --> 00:21:42.218
(COUGHING)

321
00:21:48.057 --> 00:21:49.058
Peggy.

322
00:21:54.898 --> 00:21:55.899
Steve.

323
00:21:56.733 --> 00:21:57.775
Yeah?

324
00:21:58.359 --> 00:21:59.360
(GASPS)

325
00:21:59.444 --> 00:22:00.737
You're alive.

326
00:22:01.738 --> 00:22:04.491
You came back.

327
00:22:04.741 --> 00:22:05.742
Yeah. Peggy.

328
00:22:09.287 --> 00:22:11.539
It's been so long.

329
00:22:14.083 --> 00:22:15.543
So long.

330
00:22:16.586 --> 00:22:19.130
Well. I couldn't leave my best girl.

331
00:22:19.339 --> 00:22:21.424
Not when she owes me a dance.

332
00:22:27.430 --> 00:22:28.806
Secure office.

333
00:22:36.731 --> 00:22:39.609
Open <i>Lemurian Star's</i>
satellite launch file.

334
00:22:40.652 --> 00:22:42.362
S.H.I.E.L.D. COMPUTER:
<i>Access denied.</i>

335
00:22:43.071 --> 00:22:44.072
Run decryption.

336
00:22:46.699 --> 00:22:48.618
<i>Decryption failed.</i>

337
00:22:48.785 --> 00:22:51.496
Director override. Fury. Nicholas J.

338
00:22:53.540 --> 00:22:56.543
<i>Override denied. All files sealed.</i>

339
00:22:56.751 --> 00:22:58.211
On whose authority?

340
00:22:58.419 --> 00:23:00.630
<i>Fury. Nicholas J.</i>

341
00:23:06.219 --> 00:23:07.303
World Security Council.

342
00:23:07.470 --> 00:23:08.680
<i>Confirmed.</i>

343
00:23:11.307 --> 00:23:13.601
ROCKWELL: <i>if Nick Fury thinks
he can get his costumed thugs</i>

344
00:23:13.810 --> 00:23:17.021
<i>and S.T.R.I.K.E. commandos to
mop up his mess. he's sadly mistaken.</i>

345
00:23:17.230 --> 00:23:18.398
This failure is unacceptable.

346
00:23:18.606 --> 00:23:20.191
Considering this attack took place

347
00:23:20.400 --> 00:23:22.151
one mile from my country's
sovereign waters.

348
00:23:22.318 --> 00:23:24.737
it's a bit more than that.
I move for immediate hearing.

349
00:23:24.946 --> 00:23:26.823
We don't need hearings.
we need action.

350
00:23:26.990 --> 00:23:29.117
It's this Council's duty
to oversee S.H.I.E.L.D.

351
00:23:29.409 --> 00:23:31.286
A breach like this
raises serious questions.

352
00:23:31.494 --> 00:23:33.162
Like how the hell did a French pirate

353
00:23:33.371 --> 00:23:37.250
manage to hijack a covert S.H.I.E.L.D.
vessel in broad daylight?

354
00:23:37.458 --> 00:23:39.502
For the record. Councilman.
he's Algerian.

355
00:23:40.169 --> 00:23:42.171
I can draw a map if it'd help.

356
00:23:42.338 --> 00:23:45.174
I appreciate your wit. Secretary Pierce.

357
00:23:46.009 --> 00:23:48.928
But this Council takes things
like international piracy fairly seriously.

358
00:23:49.178 --> 00:23:52.348
Really? I don't.

359
00:23:53.808 --> 00:23:56.352
I don't care about one boat.
I care about the fleet.

360
00:23:57.478 --> 00:24:00.273
If this Council is going to fall to rancour

361
00:24:00.356 --> 00:24:03.026
every time someone pushes us
on the playing field.

362
00:24:04.277 --> 00:24:06.321
maybe we need someone to oversee us.

363
00:24:06.529 --> 00:24:09.032
YEN: Mr Secretary.
nobody is suggesting...

364
00:24:13.119 --> 00:24:14.162
Excuse me.

365
00:24:14.245 --> 00:24:15.830
More trouble. Mr Secretary?

366
00:24:16.039 --> 00:24:17.624
PIERCE: Depends on your definition.

367
00:24:20.918 --> 00:24:22.420
(DOOR OPENING)

368
00:24:26.382 --> 00:24:29.469
I work 40 floors away
and it takes a hijacking for you to visit?

369
00:24:29.677 --> 00:24:31.763
A nuclear war would do it. too.

370
00:24:32.930 --> 00:24:34.182
You busy in there?

371
00:24:34.390 --> 00:24:35.892
Nothing some earmarks can't fix.

372
00:24:37.894 --> 00:24:41.189
I'm here to ask a favour.

373
00:24:41.981 --> 00:24:43.858
I want you to call for a vote.

374
00:24:44.067 --> 00:24:46.152
Project Insight has to be delayed.

375
00:24:46.569 --> 00:24:48.738
Nick. that's not a favour.

376
00:24:48.946 --> 00:24:50.448
that's a sub-committee hearing.
A long one.

377
00:24:50.657 --> 00:24:52.283
It could be nothing.
It probably is nothing.

378
00:24:52.492 --> 00:24:55.119
I just need time
to make sure it's nothing.

379
00:24:55.328 --> 00:24:56.371
But if it's something?

380
00:24:56.579 --> 00:24:59.374
Then we'll both be damn glad
those helicarriers aren't in the air.

381
00:25:01.501 --> 00:25:02.460
Fine.

382
00:25:03.211 --> 00:25:06.714
But you got to get Iron Man
to stop by my niece's birthday party.

383
00:25:07.215 --> 00:25:08.508
Thank you. sir.

384
00:25:08.716 --> 00:25:11.594
And not just a flyby. He's got to mingle.

385
00:25:14.263 --> 00:25:15.431
GARCIA: <i>The thing is.</i>

386
00:25:16.057 --> 00:25:18.017
I think it's getting worse.

387
00:25:19.268 --> 00:25:21.562
A cop pulled me over last week.

388
00:25:21.771 --> 00:25:23.022
He thought I was drunk.

389
00:25:24.190 --> 00:25:27.694
I swerved to miss a plastic bag.

390
00:25:29.112 --> 00:25:30.905
I thought it was an IED.

391
00:25:33.199 --> 00:25:35.076
WILSON: Some stuff you leave there.

392
00:25:35.410 --> 00:25:37.453
Other stuff you bring back.

393
00:25:37.620 --> 00:25:40.540
It's our job to figure out how to carry it.

394
00:25:40.748 --> 00:25:44.919
Is it gonna be in a big suitcase.
or in a little man-purse?

395
00:25:46.087 --> 00:25:47.130
It's up to you.

396
00:25:48.339 --> 00:25:49.674
- I'll see you next week.
- Definitely.

397
00:25:51.718 --> 00:25:54.011
Look who it is. the running man.

398
00:25:54.887 --> 00:25:57.306
Caught the last few minutes.
It's pretty intense.

399
00:25:57.515 --> 00:26:00.476
Yeah. brother.
we all got the same problems.

400
00:26:01.185 --> 00:26:02.395
Guilt.

401
00:26:02.854 --> 00:26:04.063
regret.

402
00:26:04.647 --> 00:26:06.190
You lose someone?

403
00:26:06.858 --> 00:26:09.235
My wingman. Riley.

404
00:26:10.236 --> 00:26:11.320
Flying a night mission.

405
00:26:11.487 --> 00:26:13.823
Standard PJ rescue op.

406
00:26:14.031 --> 00:26:16.075
Nothing we hadn't done
1.000 times before.

407
00:26:16.284 --> 00:26:19.871
Until an RPG knocked Riley's
dumb ass out of the sky.

408
00:26:21.998 --> 00:26:23.332
Nothing I could do.

409
00:26:23.916 --> 00:26:25.918
It's like I was up there just to watch.

410
00:26:27.044 --> 00:26:29.005
- I'm sorry.
- After that.

411
00:26:29.172 --> 00:26:32.800
I had a really hard time finding a reason
for being over there. you know?

412
00:26:34.761 --> 00:26:37.013
But you're happy now.
back in the world?

413
00:26:37.847 --> 00:26:41.476
The number of people giving me
orders is down to about zero.

414
00:26:41.684 --> 00:26:42.685
So. hell yeah.

415
00:26:43.811 --> 00:26:44.854
Are you thinking about getting out?

416
00:26:45.855 --> 00:26:46.856
No.

417
00:26:48.900 --> 00:26:50.026
I don't know.

418
00:26:51.569 --> 00:26:54.113
To be honest. I don't know
what I would do with myself if I did.

419
00:26:54.655 --> 00:26:55.656
- Ultimate fighting?
- (LAUGHS)

420
00:26:56.491 --> 00:26:58.868
Just a great idea off the top of my head.

421
00:26:59.035 --> 00:27:01.454
Seriously. you could do
whatever you want to do.

422
00:27:02.455 --> 00:27:03.498
What makes you happy?

423
00:27:05.416 --> 00:27:07.084
I don't know.

424
00:27:08.544 --> 00:27:11.339
ELECTRONIC VOICE: <i>Activating
communications encryption protocol.</i>

425
00:27:11.547 --> 00:27:13.841
Open secure line 0405.

426
00:27:14.300 --> 00:27:15.343
<i>Confirmed.</i>

427
00:27:16.719 --> 00:27:17.762
<i>This is Hill.</i>

428
00:27:17.929 --> 00:27:19.764
I need you here in D.C.

429
00:27:19.972 --> 00:27:22.683
Deep shadow conditions.

430
00:27:23.351 --> 00:27:24.519
<i>Give me four hours.</i>

431
00:27:24.602 --> 00:27:26.187
You have three. Over.

432
00:27:42.453 --> 00:27:44.121
Want to see my lease?

433
00:27:45.581 --> 00:27:47.250
(SIREN WAILS)

434
00:28:02.056 --> 00:28:03.266
ELECTRONIC VOICE:
<i>Fracture detected.</i>

435
00:28:03.391 --> 00:28:04.392
(GASPING)

436
00:28:06.435 --> 00:28:08.813
<i>Recommend an aesthetic injection.</i>

437
00:28:13.568 --> 00:28:16.863
<i>D.C. Metro Police dispatch
shows no units in this area.</i>

438
00:28:22.159 --> 00:28:23.202
Get me out of here.

439
00:28:25.955 --> 00:28:27.206
<i>Propulsion systems offline.</i>

440
00:28:27.331 --> 00:28:28.332
Then reboot. damn it!

441
00:28:49.061 --> 00:28:50.730
<i>Warning. Window
integrity compromised.</i>

442
00:28:50.855 --> 00:28:52.398
You think?

443
00:28:53.232 --> 00:28:55.067
(DRILLING)

444
00:28:55.860 --> 00:28:56.861
How long to propulsion?

445
00:28:56.944 --> 00:28:57.945
<i>Calculating.</i>

446
00:29:01.198 --> 00:29:04.285
<i>Window integrity 31%.
Deploying countermeasures.</i>

447
00:29:04.493 --> 00:29:05.620
Hold that order!

448
00:29:07.413 --> 00:29:09.457
<i>Window integrity 19%.</i>

449
00:29:09.665 --> 00:29:10.708
<i>Offensive measures advised.</i>

450
00:29:10.791 --> 00:29:12.126
Wait!

451
00:29:15.379 --> 00:29:17.256
<i>Window integrity 1%.</i>

452
00:29:17.340 --> 00:29:18.466
Now!

453
00:29:28.893 --> 00:29:30.519
<i>Propulsion systems now online.</i>

454
00:29:30.686 --> 00:29:31.854
Full acceleration! Now!

455
00:29:32.021 --> 00:29:33.648
(ENGINE REVVING)

456
00:29:47.912 --> 00:29:49.288
Initiate vertical takeoff!

457
00:29:49.455 --> 00:29:50.456
<i>Flight systems damaged.</i>

458
00:29:50.539 --> 00:29:52.500
Then activate guidance cameras!

459
00:29:53.709 --> 00:29:54.710
(GROANING)

460
00:29:55.878 --> 00:29:56.879
Give me the wheel!

461
00:30:04.637 --> 00:30:05.763
Get me Agent Hill.

462
00:30:05.972 --> 00:30:07.181
<i>Communications array damaged.</i>

463
00:30:07.848 --> 00:30:08.891
Well. what's not damaged?

464
00:30:09.100 --> 00:30:11.227
<i>Air conditioning is fully operational.</i>

465
00:30:23.030 --> 00:30:24.073
<i>Traffic ahead.</i>

466
00:30:24.240 --> 00:30:25.116
Give me an alternate route.

467
00:30:25.282 --> 00:30:27.034
<i>Traffic alert on Roosevelt Bridge.</i>

468
00:30:27.243 --> 00:30:28.452
<i>All vehicles stopped.</i>

469
00:30:28.661 --> 00:30:32.081
<i>17th Avenue clear in three blocks.
directly ahead.</i>

470
00:30:34.917 --> 00:30:36.377
(TYRES SCREECHING)

471
00:30:47.930 --> 00:30:49.015
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

472
00:31:13.622 --> 00:31:14.623
(GROANS)

473
00:31:34.018 --> 00:31:35.770
(CAR HORNS HONKING)

474
00:32:08.511 --> 00:32:09.720
<i>Warning. Approaching intersection.</i>

475
00:32:18.604 --> 00:32:20.856
Get me off the grid!

476
00:32:21.065 --> 00:32:22.775
<i>Calculating route to secure location.</i>

477
00:33:37.183 --> 00:33:40.436
So sweet. That is so nice.

478
00:33:41.395 --> 00:33:42.438
Hi.

479
00:33:42.688 --> 00:33:43.856
I got to go. though.

480
00:33:44.648 --> 00:33:45.858
Okay. Bye.

481
00:33:47.026 --> 00:33:48.652
My aunt. she's kind of an insomniac.

482
00:33:50.404 --> 00:33:51.405
Yeah.

483
00:33:53.032 --> 00:33:54.074
Hey. if you want...

484
00:33:54.283 --> 00:33:56.452
If you want.
you're welcome to use my machine.

485
00:33:56.660 --> 00:33:58.204
Might be cheaper
than the one in the basement.

486
00:33:59.121 --> 00:34:00.539
Oh. yeah? What's it cost?

487
00:34:01.498 --> 00:34:03.209
A cup of coffee?

488
00:34:06.253 --> 00:34:07.630
Thank you. but

489
00:34:08.214 --> 00:34:09.882
I already have a load in downstairs.

490
00:34:10.090 --> 00:34:12.927
and you really don't want
my scrubs in your machine.

491
00:34:13.135 --> 00:34:16.138
I just finished a rotation
in the infectious disease ward. so...

492
00:34:16.347 --> 00:34:18.307
Well. I'll keep my distance.

493
00:34:18.515 --> 00:34:19.642
Hopefully. not too far.

494
00:34:20.517 --> 00:34:22.519
(1940s MUSIC PLAYING
IN THE DISTANCE)

495
00:34:22.770 --> 00:34:24.188
Oh. and I think you left your stereo on.

496
00:34:24.730 --> 00:34:25.731
Oh.

497
00:34:25.814 --> 00:34:27.274
Right. Thank you.

498
00:34:27.483 --> 00:34:28.484
Yeah.

499
00:34:31.737 --> 00:34:33.614
(1940s MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING)

500
00:34:48.003 --> 00:34:50.005
(MUSIC STOPS)

501
00:34:52.758 --> 00:34:56.095
(1940s MUSIC RESUMES PLAYING)

502
00:35:14.280 --> 00:35:16.031
I don't remember giving you a key.

503
00:35:16.282 --> 00:35:17.866
(GRUNTS)

504
00:35:17.950 --> 00:35:20.035
You really think I'd need one?

505
00:35:22.037 --> 00:35:23.664
My wife kicked me out.

506
00:35:25.249 --> 00:35:26.500
I didn't know you were married.

507
00:35:28.127 --> 00:35:30.212
A lot of things you don't know about me.

508
00:35:30.963 --> 00:35:32.881
I know. Nick. That's the problem.

509
00:35:47.563 --> 00:35:51.025
I'm sorry to have to do this.
but I had no place else to crash.

510
00:35:58.282 --> 00:35:59.700
Who else knows about your wife?

511
00:36:02.411 --> 00:36:03.537
Just...

512
00:36:06.123 --> 00:36:07.875
My friends.

513
00:36:08.167 --> 00:36:09.626
Is that what we are?

514
00:36:10.336 --> 00:36:11.712
That's up to you.

515
00:36:12.546 --> 00:36:13.547
Ahh!

516
00:36:16.342 --> 00:36:17.551
(GROANING)

517
00:36:21.847 --> 00:36:23.432
(COUGHING)

518
00:36:30.189 --> 00:36:33.692
Don't trust anyone.

519
00:36:34.234 --> 00:36:36.028
(DOOR OPENS)

520
00:36:36.737 --> 00:36:37.780
KATE: Captain Rogers?

521
00:36:39.823 --> 00:36:40.824
KATE: Captain.

522
00:36:41.116 --> 00:36:43.118
I'm Agent 13 of S.H.I.E.L.D.
Special Service.

523
00:36:43.410 --> 00:36:44.453
Kate?

524
00:36:46.080 --> 00:36:47.164
I'm assigned to protect you.

525
00:36:47.373 --> 00:36:48.540
ROGERS: On whose order?

526
00:36:49.792 --> 00:36:50.793
(GASPS) His.

527
00:36:56.131 --> 00:36:57.549
Foxtrot is down. he's unresponsive.

528
00:36:57.758 --> 00:36:58.759
I need EMTs.

529
00:36:58.967 --> 00:37:00.469
DISPATCHER:
<i>Do we have a 20 on the shooter?</i>

530
00:37:01.178 --> 00:37:02.471
Tell him I'm in pursuit.

531
00:38:02.906 --> 00:38:04.116
ROMANOFF: Is he gonna make it?

532
00:38:04.199 --> 00:38:05.659
ROGERS: I don't know.

533
00:38:07.286 --> 00:38:08.704
ROMANOFF: Tell me about the shooter.

534
00:38:08.912 --> 00:38:11.039
He's fast. Strong.

535
00:38:14.001 --> 00:38:15.252
Had a metal arm.

536
00:38:20.591 --> 00:38:21.842
Ballistics?

537
00:38:22.468 --> 00:38:25.929
Three slugs. no rifling.
Completely untraceable.

538
00:38:26.138 --> 00:38:27.389
Soviet-made.

539
00:38:28.390 --> 00:38:29.391
Yeah.

540
00:38:30.476 --> 00:38:31.560
MALE NURSE: He's in V-tach.

541
00:38:31.643 --> 00:38:32.644
FEMALE NURSE: Crash cart coming in.

542
00:38:32.728 --> 00:38:33.687
DOCTOR:
Nurse. help me with the drape.

543
00:38:33.770 --> 00:38:34.897
MALE NURSE: BP's dropping.
DOCTOR: Defibrillator!

544
00:38:37.733 --> 00:38:39.151
MALE DOCTOR:
I want you to charge him at 100.

545
00:38:39.359 --> 00:38:40.736
Don't do this to me. Nick.

546
00:38:40.944 --> 00:38:42.196
Stand back.

547
00:38:42.446 --> 00:38:43.572
Three. two.

548
00:38:43.906 --> 00:38:45.491
one. Clear.

549
00:38:46.950 --> 00:38:48.327
MALE DOCTOR: Pulse?
MALE NURSE: No pulse.

550
00:38:48.619 --> 00:38:49.745
DOCTOR: Okay. 200. please.

551
00:38:49.870 --> 00:38:50.954
Stand back!

552
00:38:51.163 --> 00:38:53.415
Three. two. one. Clear!

553
00:38:53.540 --> 00:38:54.583
Get me epinephrine!

554
00:38:55.876 --> 00:38:56.835
Pulse?

555
00:38:56.919 --> 00:38:57.920
MALE NURSE: Negative.

556
00:39:00.631 --> 00:39:02.591
Don't do this to me. Nick.
Don't do this to me.

557
00:39:22.778 --> 00:39:23.904
DOCTOR: What's the time?

558
00:39:23.987 --> 00:39:25.072
FEMALE NURSE: 1 :03. Doctor.

559
00:39:27.282 --> 00:39:29.952
MALE DOCTOR:
Time of death. 1 :03 a.m.

560
00:40:07.447 --> 00:40:09.032
I need to take him.

561
00:40:23.005 --> 00:40:24.089
ROGERS: Natasha.

562
00:40:37.936 --> 00:40:38.979
Natasha!

563
00:40:40.647 --> 00:40:41.898
Why was Fury in your apartment?

564
00:40:43.734 --> 00:40:45.027
(SIGHS) I don't know.

565
00:40:45.235 --> 00:40:46.695
Cap. they want you back at S.H.I.E.L.D.

566
00:40:47.321 --> 00:40:48.363
Yeah. give me a second.

567
00:40:48.488 --> 00:40:49.489
They want you now.

568
00:40:50.824 --> 00:40:52.159
Okay.

569
00:40:55.329 --> 00:40:57.414
You're a terrible liar.

570
00:41:03.462 --> 00:41:05.130
SITWELL ON EARPIECE: <i>S.T.R.I.K.E.
team. escort Captain Rogers</i>

571
00:41:05.380 --> 00:41:07.716
<i>back to S.H.I.E.L.D.
immediately for questioning.</i>

572
00:41:07.883 --> 00:41:09.343
RUMLOW: I told him.

573
00:41:16.475 --> 00:41:17.851
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

574
00:41:19.603 --> 00:41:20.687
S.T.R.I.K.E.. move it out.

575
00:41:36.536 --> 00:41:37.579
Captain Rogers.

576
00:41:37.829 --> 00:41:39.081
Neighbour.

577
00:41:41.083 --> 00:41:42.834
PIERCE: Oh. Captain.

578
00:41:43.293 --> 00:41:44.294
I'm Alexander Pierce.

579
00:41:44.920 --> 00:41:46.338
Sir. it's an honour.

580
00:41:46.546 --> 00:41:47.589
The honour's mine. Captain.

581
00:41:47.798 --> 00:41:50.258
My father served in the 101st.
Come on in.

582
00:41:51.551 --> 00:41:54.054
PIERCE: That photo was taken
five years after Nick and I met.

583
00:41:54.262 --> 00:41:56.640
when I was at State Department
in Bogota.

584
00:41:56.848 --> 00:41:59.309
E.L.N. rebels took the embassy.

585
00:41:59.518 --> 00:42:03.772
and security got me out.
but the rebels took hostages.

586
00:42:04.231 --> 00:42:07.442
Nick was Deputy Chief
of the S.H.I.E.L.D. station there.

587
00:42:07.609 --> 00:42:08.902
and he comes to me with a plan.

588
00:42:09.111 --> 00:42:10.946
He wants to storm the building
through the sewers.

589
00:42:11.154 --> 00:42:13.907
I said. "No. we'll negotiate."

590
00:42:14.950 --> 00:42:18.495
Turned out. the E.L.N. didn't negotiate.
so they put out a kill order.

591
00:42:18.704 --> 00:42:20.831
They stormed the basement.
and what do they find?

592
00:42:21.039 --> 00:42:22.457
They find it empty.

593
00:42:23.709 --> 00:42:25.544
Nick had ignored my direct order.

594
00:42:25.752 --> 00:42:29.089
and carried out an unauthorised
military operation on foreign soil.

595
00:42:29.798 --> 00:42:31.883
and saved the lives of
a dozen political officers.

596
00:42:32.217 --> 00:42:33.301
including my daughter.

597
00:42:33.468 --> 00:42:35.053
So you gave him a promotion.

598
00:42:35.262 --> 00:42:36.805
I've never had any cause to regret it.

599
00:42:39.057 --> 00:42:41.101
Captain. why was Nick
in your apartment last night?

600
00:42:45.188 --> 00:42:46.273
I don't know.

601
00:42:47.524 --> 00:42:48.859
Did you know it was bugged?

602
00:42:49.776 --> 00:42:52.070
I did. because Nick told me.

603
00:42:52.571 --> 00:42:55.031
Did he tell you
he was the one who bugged it?

604
00:43:01.788 --> 00:43:02.998
I want you to see something.

605
00:43:03.957 --> 00:43:05.167
INTERROGATOR:
<i>Who hired you. Batroc?</i>

606
00:43:05.500 --> 00:43:06.460
Is that live?

607
00:43:06.835 --> 00:43:10.213
Yeah. they picked him up last night
in a not-so-safe house in Algiers.

608
00:43:11.339 --> 00:43:12.799
ROGERS:
Are you saying he's a suspect?

609
00:43:12.883 --> 00:43:14.509
Assassination isn't Batroc's line.

610
00:43:14.926 --> 00:43:17.512
PIERCE: No. no.
It's more complicated than that.

611
00:43:17.679 --> 00:43:20.265
Batroc was hired anonymously
to attack the <i>Lemurian Star.</i>

612
00:43:20.474 --> 00:43:23.977
And he was contacted by email
and paid by wire transfer.

613
00:43:24.686 --> 00:43:28.565
and then the money was run through
17 fictitious accounts.

614
00:43:29.191 --> 00:43:31.026
The last one going to
a holding company

615
00:43:31.193 --> 00:43:33.403
that was registered to a Jacob Veech.

616
00:43:33.612 --> 00:43:34.905
Am I supposed to know who that is?

617
00:43:35.113 --> 00:43:37.115
Not likely. Veech died six years ago.

618
00:43:37.532 --> 00:43:40.243
His last address was
1435 Elmhurst Drive.

619
00:43:40.994 --> 00:43:44.289
When I first met Nick.
his mother lived at 1437.

620
00:43:45.957 --> 00:43:49.252
Are you saying
Fury hired the pirates? Why?

621
00:43:49.753 --> 00:43:51.421
The prevailing theory

622
00:43:52.506 --> 00:43:55.300
was that the hijacking was
a cover for the acquisition

623
00:43:55.509 --> 00:43:57.886
and sale of classified intelligence.

624
00:43:59.721 --> 00:44:02.516
The sale went sour
and that led to Nick's death.

625
00:44:05.685 --> 00:44:08.438
If you really knew Nick Fury.
you'd know that's not true.

626
00:44:09.689 --> 00:44:11.775
Why do you think we're talking?

627
00:44:15.403 --> 00:44:17.948
See. I took a seat on the Council
not because I wanted to.

628
00:44:18.156 --> 00:44:21.910
but because Nick asked me to.
because we were both realists.

629
00:44:23.411 --> 00:44:27.707
We knew that. despite all the diplomacy
and the handshaking and the rhetoric.

630
00:44:28.542 --> 00:44:30.919
to build a really better world

631
00:44:31.628 --> 00:44:34.798
sometimes means having
to tear the old one down.

632
00:44:37.050 --> 00:44:38.468
And that makes enemies.

633
00:44:40.762 --> 00:44:43.640
Those people that call you dirty
because you got the guts

634
00:44:43.849 --> 00:44:46.601
to stick your hands in the mud
and try to build something better.

635
00:44:48.019 --> 00:44:50.689
And the idea that those people
could be happy today

636
00:44:52.148 --> 00:44:54.609
makes me really. really angry.

637
00:44:58.697 --> 00:45:00.866
Captain. you were the last
one to see Nick alive.

638
00:45:00.949 --> 00:45:02.951
I don't think that's an accident.

639
00:45:03.535 --> 00:45:05.120
And I don't think you do. either.

640
00:45:07.372 --> 00:45:09.165
So. I'm gonna ask again.

641
00:45:09.541 --> 00:45:11.376
Why was he there?

642
00:45:14.296 --> 00:45:16.590
He told me not to trust anyone.

643
00:45:18.842 --> 00:45:21.052
PIERCE: I wonder if that included him.

644
00:45:25.891 --> 00:45:27.142
I'm sorry.

645
00:45:27.309 --> 00:45:28.602
Those were his last words.

646
00:45:30.228 --> 00:45:31.438
Excuse me.

647
00:45:34.900 --> 00:45:36.318
Captain.

648
00:45:36.526 --> 00:45:39.529
somebody murdered my friend
and I'm gonna find out why.

649
00:45:40.572 --> 00:45:42.991
Anyone gets in my way.
they're gonna regret it.

650
00:45:44.367 --> 00:45:45.744
Anyone.

651
00:45:48.663 --> 00:45:50.123
Understood.

652
00:46:07.641 --> 00:46:09.059
Operations Control.

653
00:46:09.267 --> 00:46:10.644
S.H.I.E.L.D. COMPUTER: <i>Confirmed.</i>

654
00:46:12.020 --> 00:46:14.272
Keep all S.T.R.I.K.E. personnel on site.

655
00:46:14.356 --> 00:46:15.690
- Understood.
- Yes. sir.

656
00:46:15.899 --> 00:46:17.108
RUMLOW: Forensics.
COMPUTER: <i>Confirmed.</i>

657
00:46:17.317 --> 00:46:18.485
RUMLOW: Cap.

658
00:46:18.860 --> 00:46:19.861
Rumlow.

659
00:46:29.454 --> 00:46:32.207
Evidence Response found some fibres
on the roof they want us to see.

660
00:46:32.374 --> 00:46:33.959
You want me to get the tac team ready?

661
00:46:34.167 --> 00:46:35.710
No. let's wait and see what it is first.

662
00:46:35.877 --> 00:46:36.962
Right.

663
00:46:48.723 --> 00:46:50.517
What's the status so far?

664
00:46:51.726 --> 00:46:53.353
MAN: Administrations level.
COMPUTER: <i>Confirmed.</i>

665
00:46:53.937 --> 00:46:55.355
Excuse me.

666
00:46:55.814 --> 00:46:57.857
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

667
00:47:03.613 --> 00:47:05.865
I'm sorry about
what happened with Fury.

668
00:47:06.074 --> 00:47:08.034
It's messed up. what happened to him.

669
00:47:08.243 --> 00:47:09.577
Thank you.

670
00:47:28.513 --> 00:47:29.556
MAN: Records.

671
00:47:29.764 --> 00:47:30.890
COMPUTER: <i>Confirmed.</i>

672
00:47:46.656 --> 00:47:48.575
ROGERS: Before we get started.

673
00:47:49.284 --> 00:47:51.286
does anyone want to get out?

674
00:47:59.294 --> 00:48:00.628
(GRUNTING)

675
00:48:20.148 --> 00:48:21.191
(GROANS)

676
00:48:22.525 --> 00:48:23.693
(GRUNTING)

677
00:48:25.445 --> 00:48:27.197
Mobilise S.T.R.I.K.E. units. 25th floor.

678
00:48:42.337 --> 00:48:43.838
Whoa. big guy.

679
00:48:44.964 --> 00:48:47.634
I just want you to know. Cap.
this isn't personal!

680
00:48:55.850 --> 00:48:57.018
(PANTING)

681
00:48:59.395 --> 00:49:00.522
It kind of feels personal.

682
00:49:09.531 --> 00:49:11.533
Drop the shield
and put your hands in the air!

683
00:49:19.624 --> 00:49:20.959
(GRUNTING)

684
00:49:28.258 --> 00:49:30.718
S.T.R.I.K.E. AGENT:
Give it up. Rogers! Get that door open!

685
00:49:31.136 --> 00:49:32.554
You have nowhere to go!

686
00:49:37.517 --> 00:49:38.810
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

687
00:49:39.227 --> 00:49:40.436
(GROANING)

688
00:49:52.407 --> 00:49:53.491
Are you kidding me?

689
00:49:53.575 --> 00:49:55.702
He's headed for the garage.
Lock down the bridge.

690
00:50:07.213 --> 00:50:10.300
PILOT: <i>Stand down. Captain Rogers.
Stand down.</i>

691
00:50:10.758 --> 00:50:12.927
<i>Repeat. stand down.</i>

692
00:50:49.464 --> 00:50:50.965
SITWELL: Eyes here.

693
00:50:51.382 --> 00:50:53.259
Whatever your op is. bury it.

694
00:50:53.468 --> 00:50:54.469
This is Level One.

695
00:50:55.011 --> 00:50:56.721
Contact DOT.

696
00:50:56.930 --> 00:50:58.473
All traffic lights in the district go red.

697
00:50:58.973 --> 00:51:01.100
Shut all runways at BWI.

698
00:51:01.476 --> 00:51:03.144
IAD and Reagan.

699
00:51:03.353 --> 00:51:05.980
All security cameras in the city
go through this monitor right here.

700
00:51:07.190 --> 00:51:08.274
Scan all open sources.

701
00:51:08.858 --> 00:51:10.193
phones. computers.

702
00:51:10.526 --> 00:51:11.819
PDAs. Whatever.

703
00:51:12.654 --> 00:51:13.821
If someone tweets about this guy.

704
00:51:14.030 --> 00:51:15.073
I want to know about it.

705
00:51:15.782 --> 00:51:17.325
With all due respect.
if S.H.I.E.L.D. is conducting

706
00:51:17.575 --> 00:51:20.286
a manhunt for Captain America
we deserve to know why.

707
00:51:20.828 --> 00:51:22.205
PIERCE: Because he lied to us.

708
00:51:23.831 --> 00:51:27.335
Captain Rogers has information
regarding the death of Director Fury.

709
00:51:27.877 --> 00:51:29.462
He refused to share it.

710
00:51:30.505 --> 00:51:32.632
As difficult as this is to accept.

711
00:51:33.716 --> 00:51:37.011
Captain America is a fugitive
from S.H.I.E.L.D.

712
00:52:04.580 --> 00:52:05.623
- Where is it?
- Safe.

713
00:52:05.790 --> 00:52:07.417
- Do better.
- Where did you get it?

714
00:52:07.625 --> 00:52:08.876
Why would I tell you?

715
00:52:09.085 --> 00:52:11.129
Fury gave it to you. Why?

716
00:52:11.337 --> 00:52:12.714
- What's on it?
- I don't know.

717
00:52:12.922 --> 00:52:13.923
Stop lying.

718
00:52:14.132 --> 00:52:15.550
I only act like
I know everything. Rogers.

719
00:52:17.051 --> 00:52:18.553
I bet you knew Fury hired
the pirates. didn't you?

720
00:52:20.054 --> 00:52:22.974
Well. it makes sense. The ship was
dirty. Fury needed a way in. so do you.

721
00:52:23.182 --> 00:52:24.392
I'm not gonna ask you again.

722
00:52:26.269 --> 00:52:27.478
I know who killed Fury.

723
00:52:31.441 --> 00:52:33.901
Most of the intelligence community
doesn't believe he exists.

724
00:52:34.110 --> 00:52:36.946
The ones that do
call him the Winter Soldier.

725
00:52:37.155 --> 00:52:39.157
He's credited with over
two dozen assassinations

726
00:52:39.365 --> 00:52:41.242
in the last 50 years.

727
00:52:41.701 --> 00:52:43.244
So he's a ghost story.

728
00:52:43.619 --> 00:52:46.664
Five years ago. I was escorting
a nuclear engineer out of Iran.

729
00:52:46.873 --> 00:52:49.167
Somebody shot out
my tyres near Odessa.

730
00:52:49.375 --> 00:52:51.627
We lost control.
went straight over a cliff.

731
00:52:51.836 --> 00:52:53.129
I pulled us out.

732
00:52:53.338 --> 00:52:55.214
But the Winter Soldier was there.

733
00:52:55.965 --> 00:52:58.259
I was covering my engineer
so he shot him

734
00:52:58.593 --> 00:52:59.594
straight through me.

735
00:53:00.428 --> 00:53:01.512
Soviet slug.

736
00:53:02.138 --> 00:53:04.724
No rifling. Bye-bye. bikinis.

737
00:53:06.225 --> 00:53:08.102
Yeah. I bet you look terrible
in them now.

738
00:53:10.855 --> 00:53:13.358
Going after him is a dead end.
I know. I've tried.

739
00:53:14.734 --> 00:53:16.778
Like you said. he's a ghost story.

740
00:53:21.657 --> 00:53:23.534
Well. let's find out
what the ghost wants.

741
00:53:23.743 --> 00:53:25.870
PIERCE:
<i>Nick Fury was murdered in cold blood.</i>

742
00:53:26.371 --> 00:53:27.789
To any reasonable person.

743
00:53:27.872 --> 00:53:30.500
that would make him a martyr.
not a traitor.

744
00:53:30.583 --> 00:53:31.959
ROCKWELL:
You know what makes him a traitor?

745
00:53:32.126 --> 00:53:34.462
Hiring a mercenary
to hijack his own ship.

746
00:53:34.629 --> 00:53:36.964
SINGH: Nick Fury used your friendship

747
00:53:37.131 --> 00:53:40.176
to coerce this Council
into delaying Project Insight.

748
00:53:40.385 --> 00:53:42.637
A project he knew would expose
his own illegal operations.

749
00:53:43.012 --> 00:53:45.890
At best. he lied to you. At worst...

750
00:53:46.099 --> 00:53:48.393
Are you calling for my resignation?

751
00:53:48.601 --> 00:53:49.977
I've got a pen and paper right here.

752
00:53:50.186 --> 00:53:52.730
That discussion can be tabled
for a later time.

753
00:53:53.940 --> 00:53:55.483
But you do want to have a discussion?

754
00:53:55.650 --> 00:53:57.568
We've already had it. Mr Secretary.

755
00:53:58.653 --> 00:54:03.032
This Council moves to
immediately reactivate Project Insight.

756
00:54:04.325 --> 00:54:07.662
If you want to say something snappy.
now would be a good time.

757
00:54:13.793 --> 00:54:17.088
First rule of going on the run
is don't run. walk.

758
00:54:17.839 --> 00:54:20.174
If I run in these shoes.
they're gonna fall off.

759
00:54:23.219 --> 00:54:25.638
The drive has a Level Six homing
program. so as soon as we boot up

760
00:54:25.847 --> 00:54:27.723
S.H.I.E.L.D. will know
exactly where we are.

761
00:54:27.807 --> 00:54:28.850
How much time will we have?

762
00:54:29.308 --> 00:54:31.519
About nine minutes from

763
00:54:33.146 --> 00:54:34.188
now.

764
00:54:39.527 --> 00:54:41.154
ROMANOFF:
Fury was right about that ship.

765
00:54:41.362 --> 00:54:43.448
Somebody's trying to hide something.

766
00:54:43.656 --> 00:54:45.616
This drive is protected
by some sort of AI.

767
00:54:45.825 --> 00:54:48.202
It keeps rewriting itself
to counter my commands.

768
00:54:48.411 --> 00:54:50.037
Can you override it?

769
00:54:50.788 --> 00:54:52.748
The person who developed this
is slightly smarter than me.

770
00:54:53.416 --> 00:54:54.542
Slightly.

771
00:55:05.386 --> 00:55:06.596
I'm gonna try running a tracer.

772
00:55:07.722 --> 00:55:09.307
This is a program
that S.H.I.E.L.D. developed

773
00:55:09.515 --> 00:55:10.892
to track hostile malware.

774
00:55:11.058 --> 00:55:13.853
so if we can't read the file.

775
00:55:14.061 --> 00:55:15.646
maybe we can find out
where it came from.

776
00:55:16.230 --> 00:55:17.231
Can I help you guys with anything?

777
00:55:18.024 --> 00:55:21.611
Oh. no. My fiancé was just helping me
with some honeymoon destinations.

778
00:55:21.819 --> 00:55:23.738
Right. We're getting married.

779
00:55:23.946 --> 00:55:25.656
Congratulations. Where are
you guys thinking about going?

780
00:55:27.742 --> 00:55:29.243
- New Jersey.
- Oh.

781
00:55:34.207 --> 00:55:35.833
I have the exact same glasses.

782
00:55:36.751 --> 00:55:38.419
Wow. you two are practically twins.

783
00:55:38.669 --> 00:55:40.087
Yeah. I wish.

784
00:55:40.588 --> 00:55:41.589
Specimen.

785
00:55:42.298 --> 00:55:44.342
If you guys need anything.
I've been Aaron.

786
00:55:44.425 --> 00:55:45.426
Thank you.

787
00:55:47.929 --> 00:55:50.264
- You said nine minutes. Come on.
- Relax.

788
00:55:51.516 --> 00:55:52.600
Got it.

789
00:55:56.771 --> 00:55:57.855
You know it?

790
00:55:57.939 --> 00:55:59.482
I used to. Let's go.

791
00:56:01.651 --> 00:56:02.860
Standard tac team.

792
00:56:03.069 --> 00:56:04.403
Two behind. two across.

793
00:56:04.612 --> 00:56:06.197
and two coming straight at us.

794
00:56:06.405 --> 00:56:09.116
If they make us. I'll engage.
you hit the south escalator to the metro.

795
00:56:09.283 --> 00:56:11.244
Shut up and put your arm around me.
Laugh at something I said.

796
00:56:11.452 --> 00:56:12.662
- What?
- Do it.

797
00:56:13.329 --> 00:56:14.830
(ROGERS LAUGHING)

798
00:56:20.962 --> 00:56:21.963
Negative at the source.

799
00:56:22.129 --> 00:56:23.130
Give me a floor rundown.

800
00:56:23.631 --> 00:56:24.799
(OVER RADIO) <i>Negative on three.</i>

801
00:56:25.216 --> 00:56:26.217
(OVER RADIO) <i>Negative on two.</i>

802
00:56:26.551 --> 00:56:28.803
Snake the upper levels.
Work down to me.

803
00:56:36.852 --> 00:56:37.812
- Kiss me.
- What?

804
00:56:38.020 --> 00:56:40.022
Public displays of affection
make people very uncomfortable.

805
00:56:40.231 --> 00:56:41.357
Yes. they do.

806
00:56:50.825 --> 00:56:52.410
You still uncomfortable?

807
00:56:53.327 --> 00:56:54.829
It's not exactly the word I would use.

808
00:57:03.963 --> 00:57:06.090
Where did Captain America
learn how to steal a car?

809
00:57:07.049 --> 00:57:08.593
- Nazi Germany.
- Mmm.

810
00:57:09.010 --> 00:57:11.053
And we're borrowing.
Take your feet off the dash.

811
00:57:15.308 --> 00:57:18.853
All right. I have a question for you.
which you do not have to answer.

812
00:57:19.061 --> 00:57:20.438
I feel like. if you don't answer it though.

813
00:57:20.521 --> 00:57:21.856
- you're kind of answering it. you know.
- What?

814
00:57:22.064 --> 00:57:24.567
Was that your first kiss since 1945?

815
00:57:25.067 --> 00:57:26.527
- That bad. huh?
- I didn't say that.

816
00:57:26.694 --> 00:57:28.279
Well. it kind of sounds like
that's what you're saying.

817
00:57:28.404 --> 00:57:29.488
No. I didn't.

818
00:57:29.572 --> 00:57:31.490
I just wondered
how much practice you've had.

819
00:57:31.699 --> 00:57:33.326
- You don't need practice.
- Everybody needs practice.

820
00:57:33.534 --> 00:57:35.745
It was not my first kiss since 1945.

821
00:57:36.162 --> 00:57:37.872
I'm 95. I'm not dead.

822
00:57:38.456 --> 00:57:39.957
Nobody special. though?

823
00:57:40.041 --> 00:57:41.375
(CHUCKLES)

824
00:57:42.209 --> 00:57:43.294
Believe it or not. it's kind of hard

825
00:57:43.377 --> 00:57:45.671
to find someone with
shared life experience.

826
00:57:45.755 --> 00:57:47.340
Well. that's all right.
You just make something up.

827
00:57:47.798 --> 00:57:49.717
- What. like you?
- I don't know.

828
00:57:49.925 --> 00:57:51.052
The truth is a matter of circumstance.

829
00:57:51.218 --> 00:57:53.554
It's not all things to all people.
all the time.

830
00:57:54.889 --> 00:57:55.890
Neither am I.

831
00:57:56.641 --> 00:57:57.892
That's a tough way to live.

832
00:57:59.101 --> 00:58:01.187
It's a good way not to die. though.

833
00:58:02.063 --> 00:58:03.522
You know. it's kind of hard
to trust someone.

834
00:58:03.731 --> 00:58:05.191
when you don't know
who that someone really is.

835
00:58:06.275 --> 00:58:07.360
Yeah.

836
00:58:10.571 --> 00:58:11.656
Who do you want me to be?

837
00:58:12.615 --> 00:58:13.616
How about a friend?

838
00:58:17.078 --> 00:58:21.165
Well. there's a chance you might be
in the wrong business. Rogers.

839
00:58:36.931 --> 00:58:38.307
ROGERS: This is it.

840
00:58:39.558 --> 00:58:41.477
The file came from these coordinates.

841
00:58:42.770 --> 00:58:43.979
So did I.

842
00:58:52.154 --> 00:58:53.614
This camp is where I was trained.

843
00:58:56.659 --> 00:58:57.785
Change much?

844
00:59:00.454 --> 00:59:01.664
A little.

845
00:59:01.872 --> 00:59:03.999
DRILL SERGEANT:
Pick up the pace. ladies!

846
00:59:04.208 --> 00:59:05.793
Let's go! Let's go!

847
00:59:06.627 --> 00:59:07.878
Double time!

848
00:59:09.171 --> 00:59:11.173
Come on. Rogers. move it!

849
00:59:15.219 --> 00:59:16.512
Come on. fall in!

850
00:59:17.555 --> 00:59:18.639
Rogers!

851
00:59:19.098 --> 00:59:20.307
I said fall in!

852
00:59:22.643 --> 00:59:23.811
ROMANOFF: This is a dead end.

853
00:59:23.978 --> 00:59:26.772
Zero heat signatures.
zero waves. not even radio.

854
00:59:28.190 --> 00:59:31.026
Whoever wrote the file must
have used a router to throw people off.

855
00:59:32.987 --> 00:59:33.988
What is it?

856
00:59:34.196 --> 00:59:35.990
ROGERS: Army regulations
forbid storing munitions

857
00:59:36.198 --> 00:59:38.117
within 500 yards of the barracks.

858
00:59:38.909 --> 00:59:40.953
This building is in the wrong place.

859
00:59:56.343 --> 00:59:58.179
ROMANOFF: This is S.H.I.E.L.D.

860
00:59:59.054 --> 01:00:00.973
Maybe where it started.

861
01:00:19.033 --> 01:00:20.743
And there's Stark's father.

862
01:00:21.368 --> 01:00:22.703
ROGERS: Howard.

863
01:00:24.038 --> 01:00:25.289
Who's the girl?

864
01:00:44.683 --> 01:00:47.019
If you're already working
in a secret office.

865
01:00:57.571 --> 01:00:59.156
why do you need to hide the elevator?

866
01:00:59.240 --> 01:01:00.241
(MACHINE BLEEPING)

867
01:01:07.581 --> 01:01:08.874
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

868
01:01:50.875 --> 01:01:54.628
This can't be the data point.
This technology is ancient.

869
01:02:19.153 --> 01:02:21.572
(ELECTRONIC VOICE SPEAKING)

870
01:02:24.617 --> 01:02:26.619
Y-E-S spells yes.

871
01:02:27.578 --> 01:02:29.163
(POWERING UP)

872
01:02:30.664 --> 01:02:32.583
Shall we play a game?

873
01:02:33.208 --> 01:02:35.586
- It's from a movie that was really...
- I know. I saw it.

874
01:02:36.170 --> 01:02:37.171
(COMPUTER BEEPING)

875
01:02:41.842 --> 01:02:43.802
<i>Rogers. Steven.</i>

876
01:02:44.845 --> 01:02:46.513
<i>born 1918.</i>

877
01:02:49.683 --> 01:02:52.394
<i>Romanoff Natalia Alianovna.</i>

878
01:02:52.603 --> 01:02:54.438
<i>born 1984.</i>

879
01:02:54.647 --> 01:02:55.981
It's some kind of recording.

880
01:02:56.190 --> 01:02:58.525
<i>I am not a recording.</i> Fräulein.

881
01:02:59.193 --> 01:03:00.903
<i>I may not be the man I was</i>

882
01:03:01.195 --> 01:03:04.365
<i>when the Captain took me
prisoner in 1945.</i>

883
01:03:04.865 --> 01:03:06.492
<i>But I am.</i>

884
01:03:08.327 --> 01:03:09.745
You know this thing?

885
01:03:13.165 --> 01:03:16.168
ROGERS: Arnim Zola was a German
scientist who worked for the Red Skull.

886
01:03:16.543 --> 01:03:17.586
He's been dead for years.

887
01:03:17.795 --> 01:03:20.089
ZOLA: <i>First correction. I am Swiss.</i>

888
01:03:20.506 --> 01:03:22.883
<i>Second. look around you.</i>

889
01:03:23.050 --> 01:03:25.678
<i>I have never been more alive.</i>

890
01:03:26.220 --> 01:03:30.516
<i>In 1972.
I received a terminal diagnosis.</i>

891
01:03:30.724 --> 01:03:33.477
<i>Science could not save my body.</i>

892
01:03:33.769 --> 01:03:37.898
<i>My mind. however.
that was worth saving.</i>

893
01:03:38.107 --> 01:03:41.860
<i>on 200.000 feet of data banks.</i>

894
01:03:42.069 --> 01:03:45.656
<i>You are standing in my brain.</i>

895
01:03:45.864 --> 01:03:48.075
- ROGERS: How did you get here?
- <i>invited.</i>

896
01:03:48.701 --> 01:03:50.911
It was Operation Paperclip
after World War ll.

897
01:03:51.120 --> 01:03:54.748
S.H.I.E.L.D. recruited
German scientists with strategic value.

898
01:03:54.915 --> 01:03:57.084
ZOLA:
<i>They thought I could help their cause.</i>

899
01:03:57.251 --> 01:03:59.128
<i>I also helped my own.</i>

900
01:03:59.336 --> 01:04:00.838
ROGERS:
HYDRA died with the Red Skull.

901
01:04:01.046 --> 01:04:04.925
<i>Cut off one head.
two more shall take its place.</i>

902
01:04:05.342 --> 01:04:06.760
Prove it.

903
01:04:08.137 --> 01:04:10.055
<i>Accessing archive.</i>

904
01:04:10.597 --> 01:04:13.934
<i>HYDRA was founded on
the belief that humanity</i>

905
01:04:14.101 --> 01:04:17.271
<i>could not be trusted
with its own freedom.</i>

906
01:04:17.479 --> 01:04:20.149
<i>What we did not realise was
that if you try</i>

907
01:04:20.357 --> 01:04:23.152
<i>to take that freedom. they resist.</i>

908
01:04:24.028 --> 01:04:25.571
<i>The war taught us much.</i>

909
01:04:26.155 --> 01:04:29.450
<i>Humanity needed to surrender
its freedom willingly.</i>

910
01:04:30.617 --> 01:04:33.328
<i>After the war.
S.H.I.E.L.D. was founded.</i>

911
01:04:33.537 --> 01:04:35.622
<i>and I was recruited.</i>

912
01:04:36.081 --> 01:04:38.083
<i>The new HYDRA grew.</i>

913
01:04:38.292 --> 01:04:42.546
<i>A beautiful parasite inside S.H.I.E.L.D.</i>

914
01:04:42.963 --> 01:04:44.631
<i>For 70 years.</i>

915
01:04:44.798 --> 01:04:50.429
<i>HYDRA has been secretly
feeding crisis. reaping war.</i>

916
01:04:50.637 --> 01:04:53.307
<i>and when history did not cooperate.</i>

917
01:04:54.141 --> 01:04:55.809
<i>history was changed.</i>

918
01:04:56.143 --> 01:04:58.312
That's impossible.
S.H.I.E.L.D. would have stopped you.

919
01:04:58.437 --> 01:05:00.856
<i>Accidents will happen.</i>

920
01:05:02.858 --> 01:05:05.652
<i>HYDRA created a world so chaotic</i>

921
01:05:05.861 --> 01:05:09.698
<i>that humanity is finally ready
to sacrifice its freedom</i>

922
01:05:10.032 --> 01:05:12.034
<i>to gain its security.</i>

923
01:05:12.826 --> 01:05:16.080
<i>Once a purification process
is complete.</i>

924
01:05:16.622 --> 01:05:20.000
<i>HYDRA's new world order will arise.</i>

925
01:05:20.918 --> 01:05:22.836
<i>We won. Captain.</i>

926
01:05:23.003 --> 01:05:26.507
<i>Your death amounts to
the same as your life.</i>

927
01:05:27.007 --> 01:05:28.050
<i>A zero sum.</i>

928
01:05:28.675 --> 01:05:29.885
(GRUNTS)

929
01:05:29.968 --> 01:05:31.178
(COMPUTER BEEPS)

930
01:05:31.678 --> 01:05:33.555
<i>As I was saying...</i>

931
01:05:34.389 --> 01:05:35.432
What's on this drive?

932
01:05:35.682 --> 01:05:38.936
<i>Project Insight requires insight.</i>

933
01:05:39.394 --> 01:05:41.939
<i>So. I wrote an algorithm.</i>

934
01:05:42.314 --> 01:05:43.607
What kind of algorithm?
What does it do?

935
01:05:43.690 --> 01:05:46.193
<i>The answer to your question
is fascinating.</i>

936
01:05:46.652 --> 01:05:50.697
<i>Unfortunately. you shall
be too dead to hear it.</i>

937
01:05:50.864 --> 01:05:52.157
(DOOR CLOSING)

938
01:05:53.909 --> 01:05:55.369
(CELL PHONE BEEPING)

939
01:05:56.537 --> 01:05:57.955
Steve. we got a bogey.

940
01:05:58.413 --> 01:05:59.957
Short range ballistic.

941
01:06:00.290 --> 01:06:01.959
- 30 seconds tops.
- Who fired it?

942
01:06:02.042 --> 01:06:03.043
S.H.I.E.L.D.

943
01:06:03.210 --> 01:06:06.964
<i>I am afraid
I have been stalling. Captain.</i>

944
01:06:07.464 --> 01:06:08.549
<i>Admit it.</i>

945
01:06:08.715 --> 01:06:10.968
<i>It's better this way.</i>

946
01:06:11.176 --> 01:06:12.553
<i>We are. both of us.</i>

947
01:06:13.887 --> 01:06:15.139
<i>out of time.</i>

948
01:06:31.071 --> 01:06:33.157
(DEBRIS SETTLING)

949
01:06:41.582 --> 01:06:43.792
(ROGERS GROANING)

950
01:06:43.876 --> 01:06:45.836
(GRUNTING)

951
01:06:50.507 --> 01:06:52.259
(PANTING)

952
01:06:52.342 --> 01:06:54.303
(COUGHING)

953
01:07:38.555 --> 01:07:40.098
Call in the asset.

954
01:07:56.323 --> 01:07:57.699
RENATA: I'm going to go. Mr Pierce.

955
01:07:58.242 --> 01:08:00.035
You need anything before I leave?

956
01:08:00.827 --> 01:08:04.122
No... Uh. it's fine. Renata.
you can go home.

957
01:08:04.748 --> 01:08:06.458
Okay. Night-night.

958
01:08:06.667 --> 01:08:08.335
Good night.

959
01:08:10.963 --> 01:08:12.422
(DOOR CLOSES)

960
01:08:13.465 --> 01:08:14.841
Want some milk?

961
01:08:24.476 --> 01:08:26.311
The timetable has moved.

962
01:08:28.480 --> 01:08:30.190
Our window is limited.

963
01:08:34.236 --> 01:08:36.363
Two targets. Level Six.

964
01:08:37.823 --> 01:08:40.033
They already cost me Zola.

965
01:08:40.242 --> 01:08:42.452
I want confirmed death in 10 hours.

966
01:08:44.413 --> 01:08:46.540
Sorry. Mr Pierce. I...

967
01:08:47.040 --> 01:08:48.333
I forgot my

968
01:08:48.542 --> 01:08:49.668
phone.

969
01:08:54.715 --> 01:08:57.843
Oh. Renata.
I wish you would have knocked.

970
01:08:59.052 --> 01:09:00.554
- (GUN FIRING)
- (RENATA SHRIEKS)

971
01:09:11.690 --> 01:09:12.941
(PANTING)

972
01:09:13.358 --> 01:09:15.360
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

973
01:09:22.409 --> 01:09:23.493
Hey. man.

974
01:09:23.577 --> 01:09:27.080
I'm sorry about this.
We need a place to lay low.

975
01:09:27.289 --> 01:09:28.915
Everyone we know is trying to kill us.

976
01:09:31.877 --> 01:09:33.378
Not everyone.

977
01:09:50.354 --> 01:09:52.022
- You okay?
- Yeah.

978
01:10:00.947 --> 01:10:02.449
What's going on?

979
01:10:05.702 --> 01:10:09.122
When I first joined S.H.I.E.L.D.
I thought I was going straight.

980
01:10:12.959 --> 01:10:15.879
But I guess I just traded in
the KGB for HYDRA.

981
01:10:20.550 --> 01:10:21.551
(SIGHS)

982
01:10:21.760 --> 01:10:23.845
I thought I knew whose lies I was telling.

983
01:10:27.641 --> 01:10:30.394
but I guess I can't tell
the difference any more.

984
01:10:31.436 --> 01:10:33.355
There's a chance you might be
in the wrong business.

985
01:10:38.652 --> 01:10:39.736
I owe you.

986
01:10:41.279 --> 01:10:42.322
It's okay.

987
01:10:42.864 --> 01:10:45.075
If it was the other way around.

988
01:10:46.326 --> 01:10:47.786
and it was down to me to save your life.

989
01:10:47.994 --> 01:10:49.496
now you be honest with me.

990
01:10:51.665 --> 01:10:53.542
would you trust me to do it?

991
01:10:55.710 --> 01:10:56.711
I would now.

992
01:10:59.756 --> 01:11:01.508
And I'm always honest.

993
01:11:02.843 --> 01:11:03.969
Well. you seem pretty chipper

994
01:11:04.177 --> 01:11:05.846
for someone who just found out
they died for nothing.

995
01:11:06.763 --> 01:11:10.434
Well. guess I just like to
know who I'm fighting.

996
01:11:11.309 --> 01:11:12.310
WILSON: I made breakfast.

997
01:11:12.978 --> 01:11:15.897
If you guys eat that sort of thing.

998
01:11:17.482 --> 01:11:18.859
So. the question is.

999
01:11:19.025 --> 01:11:21.027
who at S.H.I.E.L.D. could launch
a domestic missile strike?

1000
01:11:23.113 --> 01:11:24.114
Pierce.

1001
01:11:24.406 --> 01:11:27.033
Who happens to be sitting on top
of the most secure building in the world.

1002
01:11:27.200 --> 01:11:28.368
But he's not working alone.

1003
01:11:28.577 --> 01:11:30.871
Zola's algorithm
was on the <i>Lemurian Star.</i>

1004
01:11:32.038 --> 01:11:33.540
So was Jasper Sitwell.

1005
01:11:37.210 --> 01:11:39.504
So. the real question is.
how do the two most wanted people

1006
01:11:39.713 --> 01:11:42.632
in Washington kidnap
a S.H.I.E.L.D. officer in broad daylight?

1007
01:11:43.467 --> 01:11:45.343
The answer is. you don't.

1008
01:11:46.303 --> 01:11:48.054
- What's this?
- Call it a résumé.

1009
01:11:51.725 --> 01:11:53.268
Is this Bakhmala?

1010
01:11:53.477 --> 01:11:54.895
The Khalid Khandil mission.
that was you?

1011
01:11:56.646 --> 01:11:58.023
You didn't say he was a Pararescue.

1012
01:11:59.816 --> 01:12:01.902
- Is this Riley?
- Yeah.

1013
01:12:02.110 --> 01:12:04.362
ROMANOFF: I heard they couldn't bring
in the choppers because of the RPGs.

1014
01:12:04.821 --> 01:12:05.780
What did you use? A stealth chute?

1015
01:12:05.864 --> 01:12:06.907
No.

1016
01:12:07.657 --> 01:12:09.075
These.

1017
01:12:13.997 --> 01:12:15.290
I thought you said you were a pilot.

1018
01:12:15.582 --> 01:12:16.917
I never said pilot.

1019
01:12:20.921 --> 01:12:22.672
I can't ask you to do this. Sam.

1020
01:12:23.298 --> 01:12:24.716
You got out for a good reason.

1021
01:12:24.925 --> 01:12:26.426
Dude. Captain America needs my help.

1022
01:12:26.635 --> 01:12:28.178
There's no better reason to get back in.

1023
01:12:31.932 --> 01:12:33.600
Where can we get our hands on
one of these things?

1024
01:12:33.808 --> 01:12:34.935
The last one is at Fort Meade.

1025
01:12:35.977 --> 01:12:38.480
Behind three guarded gates
and a 12-inch steel wall.

1026
01:12:41.525 --> 01:12:42.651
Shouldn't be a problem.

1027
01:12:44.361 --> 01:12:45.946
Listen. I got to fly home tonight

1028
01:12:46.154 --> 01:12:48.949
because I got
some constituency problem

1029
01:12:49.115 --> 01:12:51.034
and I got to press the flesh.

1030
01:12:51.243 --> 01:12:53.537
Any constituent in particular.
Mr Senator?

1031
01:12:54.079 --> 01:12:55.497
Oh. no. not really.

1032
01:12:56.456 --> 01:12:58.333
Twenty-three. kind of hot.

1033
01:12:59.000 --> 01:13:00.126
Real hot. you know?

1034
01:13:00.335 --> 01:13:02.462
Wants to be a reporter. I think.
I don't know.

1035
01:13:02.671 --> 01:13:03.672
Who listens at that point?

1036
01:13:03.880 --> 01:13:05.507
Doesn't sound like
much of a problem to me.

1037
01:13:05.715 --> 01:13:07.801
Really? Because she's killing my back.

1038
01:13:08.760 --> 01:13:10.512
But this isn't the place to talk about it.

1039
01:13:10.720 --> 01:13:11.763
This is a nice pin.

1040
01:13:13.056 --> 01:13:15.141
- Thank you.
- Come here.

1041
01:13:15.976 --> 01:13:17.310
(WHISPERS) Hail HYDRA.

1042
01:13:20.480 --> 01:13:22.315
- See. it's right there...
- Yeah. I just saw that.

1043
01:13:23.233 --> 01:13:24.776
- Should I get it checked?
- I think you should.

1044
01:13:27.404 --> 01:13:28.905
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

1045
01:13:33.535 --> 01:13:34.661
I need a minute.

1046
01:13:34.869 --> 01:13:36.538
Bring the car around.

1047
01:13:40.166 --> 01:13:41.334
Yes. sir?

1048
01:13:41.418 --> 01:13:43.086
WILSON:
<i>Agent Sitwell. how was lunch?</i>

1049
01:13:43.295 --> 01:13:45.880
<i>I hear the crab cakes here
are delicious.</i>

1050
01:13:46.006 --> 01:13:47.048
Who is this?

1051
01:13:47.215 --> 01:13:49.884
<i>The good-looking guy in the
sunglasses. your 10 o' clock.</i>

1052
01:13:52.012 --> 01:13:53.138
<i>Your other 10 o' clock.</i>

1053
01:13:55.015 --> 01:13:56.016
<i>There you go.</i>

1054
01:13:58.852 --> 01:14:00.353
What do you want?

1055
01:14:00.562 --> 01:14:02.355
<i>You're gonna go around
the corner to your right.</i>

1056
01:14:02.564 --> 01:14:05.066
There's a grey car two spaces down.

1057
01:14:05.275 --> 01:14:07.110
You and I are gonna take a ride.

1058
01:14:07.319 --> 01:14:09.029
And why would I do that?

1059
01:14:09.195 --> 01:14:11.781
Because that tie looks really expensive.

1060
01:14:12.240 --> 01:14:14.200
<i>and I'd hate to mess it up.</i>

1061
01:14:20.874 --> 01:14:22.709
(GRUNTING)

1062
01:14:23.793 --> 01:14:25.045
Tell me about Zola's algorithm.

1063
01:14:26.129 --> 01:14:27.130
Never heard of it.

1064
01:14:27.213 --> 01:14:28.256
What were you doing
on the <i>Lemurian Star?</i>

1065
01:14:28.340 --> 01:14:30.050
I was throwing up. I get seasick.

1066
01:14:30.842 --> 01:14:32.052
(GASPS)

1067
01:14:35.221 --> 01:14:38.433
Is this little display meant to insinuate
that you're gonna throw me off the roof?

1068
01:14:39.559 --> 01:14:40.977
Because it's really not
your style. Rogers.

1069
01:14:42.228 --> 01:14:43.229
You're right.

1070
01:14:44.105 --> 01:14:45.148
It's not.

1071
01:14:45.690 --> 01:14:46.691
It's hers.

1072
01:14:48.234 --> 01:14:49.486
(SCREAMING)

1073
01:14:50.612 --> 01:14:53.198
Oh. wait. What about that girl
from Accounting. Laura...

1074
01:14:53.740 --> 01:14:55.575
Lillian. Lip piercing. right?

1075
01:14:55.659 --> 01:14:56.826
Yeah. she's cute.

1076
01:14:56.910 --> 01:14:58.411
Yeah. I'm not ready for that.

1077
01:14:58.578 --> 01:15:00.664
(CONTINUES SCREAMING)

1078
01:15:01.081 --> 01:15:02.332
(GROANS)

1079
01:15:10.298 --> 01:15:12.342
Zola's algorithm is a program

1080
01:15:14.052 --> 01:15:15.136
for choosing

1081
01:15:15.345 --> 01:15:16.888
- Insight's targets.
- What targets?

1082
01:15:17.263 --> 01:15:18.348
You!

1083
01:15:19.349 --> 01:15:21.726
A TV anchor in Cairo.
the Under Secretary of Defence.

1084
01:15:21.935 --> 01:15:24.354
a high school valedictorian in Iowa City.

1085
01:15:24.604 --> 01:15:26.523
Bruce Banner. Stephen Strange.
anyone who's a threat

1086
01:15:26.940 --> 01:15:28.525
to HYDRA.

1087
01:15:28.733 --> 01:15:30.443
Now. or in the future.

1088
01:15:30.777 --> 01:15:32.529
In the future? How could it know?

1089
01:15:34.531 --> 01:15:35.865
(LAUGHING)

1090
01:15:36.116 --> 01:15:37.158
How could it not?

1091
01:15:39.285 --> 01:15:42.622
The 21st century is a digital book.

1092
01:15:43.957 --> 01:15:45.792
Zola taught HYDRA how to read it.

1093
01:15:48.712 --> 01:15:49.838
Your bank records.

1094
01:15:50.296 --> 01:15:51.673
medical histories. voting patterns.

1095
01:15:51.881 --> 01:15:54.300
emails. phone calls.
your damn SAT scores!

1096
01:15:55.844 --> 01:15:59.180
Zola's algorithm
evaluates people's past

1097
01:16:00.098 --> 01:16:01.307
to predict their future.

1098
01:16:01.641 --> 01:16:02.684
And what then?

1099
01:16:06.104 --> 01:16:07.897
Oh. my God. Pierce is gonna kill me.

1100
01:16:07.981 --> 01:16:09.524
What then?

1101
01:16:12.110 --> 01:16:15.196
Then the Insight helicarriers
scratch people off the list.

1102
01:16:17.449 --> 01:16:19.284
A few million at a time.

1103
01:16:26.916 --> 01:16:28.001
SITWELL: HYDRA doesn't like leaks.

1104
01:16:28.168 --> 01:16:29.836
Then why don't you try
sticking a cork in it?

1105
01:16:30.044 --> 01:16:31.337
Insight's launching in 16 hours.

1106
01:16:31.504 --> 01:16:32.547
We're cutting it a little bit close here.

1107
01:16:32.756 --> 01:16:34.674
I know.
We'll use him to bypass the DNA scans

1108
01:16:34.841 --> 01:16:36.259
and access the helicarriers directly.

1109
01:16:36.468 --> 01:16:37.510
What? Are you crazy?

1110
01:16:38.386 --> 01:16:40.138
- That is a terrible. terrible idea.
- (THUD)

1111
01:16:41.514 --> 01:16:42.766
(SCREAMING)

1112
01:16:49.355 --> 01:16:50.732
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

1113
01:17:16.049 --> 01:17:18.051
(BRAKES SQUEALING)

1114
01:17:23.807 --> 01:17:25.016
(SCREAMING) Shit!

1115
01:17:36.402 --> 01:17:37.779
ROGERS: Hang on!

1116
01:17:37.862 --> 01:17:38.905
(GRUNTS)

1117
01:17:51.042 --> 01:17:52.043
(BRAKES SCREECH)

1118
01:18:02.762 --> 01:18:03.972
(HORN BLARES)

1119
01:18:04.138 --> 01:18:05.348
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1120
01:18:46.014 --> 01:18:47.098
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1121
01:19:16.502 --> 01:19:17.962
(WINTER SOLDIER
SPEAKING RUSSIAN)

1122
01:19:18.171 --> 01:19:21.132
I have her. Find him.

1123
01:20:01.130 --> 01:20:02.215
(GRUNTS)

1124
01:20:03.216 --> 01:20:04.425
(SCREAMS)

1125
01:20:26.406 --> 01:20:27.407
Go! I got this!

1126
01:20:27.782 --> 01:20:28.825
(SIRENS WAILING)

1127
01:20:45.425 --> 01:20:46.884
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1128
01:20:55.268 --> 01:20:56.269
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

1129
01:21:07.447 --> 01:21:09.115
ROMANOFF: <i>Taking fire above
and below expressway.</i>

1130
01:21:09.282 --> 01:21:11.743
<i>Civilians threatened.
Repeat. civilians threatened.</i>

1131
01:21:15.913 --> 01:21:18.624
<i>I make an LZ.
2300 block of Virginia Avenue.</i>

1132
01:21:18.791 --> 01:21:19.876
<i>Rendezvous. two minutes.</i>

1133
01:21:45.318 --> 01:21:46.319
Get out of the way!

1134
01:21:46.861 --> 01:21:48.488
Stay out of the way!

1135
01:21:49.947 --> 01:21:51.407
- (GUNSHOT)
- Ahh!

1136
01:23:35.553 --> 01:23:36.596
Bucky?

1137
01:23:37.180 --> 01:23:38.598
Who the hell is Bucky?

1138
01:23:51.569 --> 01:23:53.154
(SIRENS WAILING)

1139
01:24:07.293 --> 01:24:08.794
Drop the shield. Cap!
Get on your knees!

1140
01:24:08.961 --> 01:24:10.421
- Get on your knees!
- (ALL SHOUTING)

1141
01:24:10.630 --> 01:24:13.216
Get down. get down! Get on your knees!

1142
01:24:13.299 --> 01:24:14.425
Down!

1143
01:24:14.967 --> 01:24:15.968
Don't move.

1144
01:24:22.975 --> 01:24:24.227
Put the gun down.

1145
01:24:24.435 --> 01:24:26.354
Not here. Not here!

1146
01:24:41.869 --> 01:24:42.912
ROGERS: <i>It was him.</i>

1147
01:24:46.165 --> 01:24:49.669
He looked right at me
like he didn't even know me.

1148
01:24:50.211 --> 01:24:52.922
How is that even possible?
It was. like. 70 years ago.

1149
01:24:53.130 --> 01:24:54.340
Zola.

1150
01:24:54.507 --> 01:24:56.133
Bucky's whole unit was captured in '43.

1151
01:24:56.342 --> 01:24:58.177
Zola experimented on him.

1152
01:24:58.386 --> 01:25:00.680
Whatever he did
helped Bucky survive the fall.

1153
01:25:02.390 --> 01:25:03.683
They must have found him and...

1154
01:25:03.766 --> 01:25:05.685
None of that's your fault. Steve.

1155
01:25:09.313 --> 01:25:11.023
Even when I had nothing. I had Bucky.

1156
01:25:14.360 --> 01:25:16.070
We need to get a doctor here.

1157
01:25:16.279 --> 01:25:17.280
If we don't put pressure on that wound.

1158
01:25:17.488 --> 01:25:18.781
she's gonna bleed out here in the truck.

1159
01:25:22.368 --> 01:25:23.703
(GROANING)

1160
01:25:26.372 --> 01:25:29.500
Ah. That thing was squeezing my brain.

1161
01:25:32.586 --> 01:25:33.671
Who is this guy?

1162
01:25:44.473 --> 01:25:46.434
Three holes. Start digging.

1163
01:26:13.586 --> 01:26:15.504
HILL: GSW. She's lost at least a pint.

1164
01:26:15.713 --> 01:26:16.922
WILSON: Maybe two.

1165
01:26:17.089 --> 01:26:19.091
- Let me take her.
- She'll want to see him first.

1166
01:26:29.018 --> 01:26:31.228
About damn time.

1167
01:26:33.189 --> 01:26:34.815
Lacerated spinal column.

1168
01:26:35.441 --> 01:26:36.776
cracked sternum.

1169
01:26:36.859 --> 01:26:38.444
shattered collarbone.

1170
01:26:38.611 --> 01:26:40.279
perforated liver.

1171
01:26:40.446 --> 01:26:42.198
and one hell of a headache.

1172
01:26:42.448 --> 01:26:43.783
Don't forget your collapsed lung.

1173
01:26:43.991 --> 01:26:45.284
Let's not forget that.

1174
01:26:45.493 --> 01:26:47.119
Otherwise. I'm good.

1175
01:26:47.495 --> 01:26:49.622
They cut you open. Your heart stopped.

1176
01:26:49.830 --> 01:26:51.874
Tetrodotoxin B.

1177
01:26:52.083 --> 01:26:54.043
Slows the pulse to one beat a minute.

1178
01:26:54.251 --> 01:26:56.045
Banner developed it for stress.

1179
01:26:56.253 --> 01:26:58.839
Didn't work so great for him.
but we found a use for it.

1180
01:26:59.048 --> 01:27:00.925
Why all the secrecy?
Why not just tell us?

1181
01:27:01.133 --> 01:27:03.386
Any attempt on the Director's
life had to look successful.

1182
01:27:03.886 --> 01:27:06.097
Can't kill you if you're already dead.

1183
01:27:06.430 --> 01:27:07.515
Besides.

1184
01:27:08.808 --> 01:27:10.309
I wasn't sure who to trust.

1185
01:27:25.825 --> 01:27:27.159
Sergeant Barnes.

1186
01:27:29.328 --> 01:27:30.329
Bucky. no!

1187
01:27:30.454 --> 01:27:31.747
(BUCKY SCREAMING)

1188
01:27:34.041 --> 01:27:37.128
ZOLA:
<i>The procedure has already started.</i>

1189
01:27:41.006 --> 01:27:44.677
<i>You are to be the new fist of HYDRA.</i>

1190
01:27:45.094 --> 01:27:46.095
<i>Put him on ice.</i>

1191
01:27:57.481 --> 01:27:58.482
Sir.

1192
01:27:59.191 --> 01:28:00.693
(STAMMERS) He's unstable.

1193
01:28:01.193 --> 01:28:02.611
Erratic.

1194
01:28:15.875 --> 01:28:16.959
Mission report.

1195
01:28:20.463 --> 01:28:21.797
Mission report now.

1196
01:28:34.602 --> 01:28:36.020
The man on the bridge.

1197
01:28:37.563 --> 01:28:38.939
(INAUDIBLE)

1198
01:28:39.148 --> 01:28:40.399
Who was he?

1199
01:28:41.817 --> 01:28:44.069
You met him earlier this week
on another assignment.

1200
01:28:47.156 --> 01:28:48.491
I knew him.

1201
01:28:57.082 --> 01:28:59.752
Your work has been a gift to mankind.

1202
01:29:02.046 --> 01:29:03.422
You shaped the century.

1203
01:29:04.131 --> 01:29:06.592
And I need you to do it one more time.

1204
01:29:07.885 --> 01:29:11.555
Society's at a tipping point
between order and chaos.

1205
01:29:11.764 --> 01:29:14.433
And tomorrow morning.
we're gonna give it a push.

1206
01:29:15.559 --> 01:29:18.771
But. if you don't do your part.
I can't do mine.

1207
01:29:20.439 --> 01:29:23.275
And HYDRA can't give the world
the freedom it deserves.

1208
01:29:26.320 --> 01:29:27.905
But I knew him.

1209
01:29:28.447 --> 01:29:29.615
(SIGHS)

1210
01:29:34.453 --> 01:29:35.955
PIERCE: Prep him.

1211
01:29:36.163 --> 01:29:38.749
He's been out of cryo freeze too long.

1212
01:29:38.958 --> 01:29:40.960
Then wipe him and start over.

1213
01:30:09.154 --> 01:30:11.031
(SCREAMING)

1214
01:30:22.668 --> 01:30:26.255
This man declined
the Nobel Peace Prize.

1215
01:30:27.006 --> 01:30:30.259
He said peace wasn't an achievement.

1216
01:30:30.718 --> 01:30:32.803
it was a responsibility.

1217
01:30:33.804 --> 01:30:37.057
See. it's stuff like this
that gives me trust issues.

1218
01:30:37.808 --> 01:30:39.059
We have to stop the launch.

1219
01:30:40.019 --> 01:30:42.771
I don't think the Council's
accepting my calls any more.

1220
01:30:45.274 --> 01:30:46.358
What's that?

1221
01:30:46.734 --> 01:30:49.403
Once the helicarriers reach 3.000 feet.

1222
01:30:49.486 --> 01:30:52.823
they'll triangulate with Insight satellites.
becoming fully weaponised.

1223
01:30:53.532 --> 01:30:55.200
FURY: We need to breach those carriers

1224
01:30:55.409 --> 01:30:57.953
and replace their targeting
blades with our own.

1225
01:30:58.037 --> 01:30:59.038
HILL: One or two won't cut it.

1226
01:30:59.246 --> 01:31:01.749
We need to link all three
carriers for this to work.

1227
01:31:01.957 --> 01:31:05.294
because if even one of those
ships remains operational.

1228
01:31:05.502 --> 01:31:07.296
a whole lot of people are gonna die.

1229
01:31:07.504 --> 01:31:10.674
We have to assume everyone aboard
those carriers is HYDRA.

1230
01:31:11.008 --> 01:31:13.093
We have to get past them.
insert these server blades.

1231
01:31:13.302 --> 01:31:16.388
And maybe. just maybe
we can salvage what's left...

1232
01:31:16.597 --> 01:31:17.598
ROGERS:
We're not salvaging anything.

1233
01:31:17.806 --> 01:31:19.058
We're not just
taking down the carriers. Nick.

1234
01:31:19.266 --> 01:31:20.309
We're taking down S.H.I.E.L.D.

1235
01:31:20.392 --> 01:31:21.685
S.H.I.E.L.D. had nothing to do with this.

1236
01:31:21.894 --> 01:31:24.063
You gave me this mission.
This is how it ends.

1237
01:31:24.188 --> 01:31:26.231
S.H.I.E.L.D.'s been compromised.
You said so yourself.

1238
01:31:26.523 --> 01:31:28.233
HYDRA grew right under your nose
and nobody noticed.

1239
01:31:28.400 --> 01:31:31.570
Why do you think we're meeting
in this cave? I noticed.

1240
01:31:31.904 --> 01:31:33.614
How many paid the price
before you did?

1241
01:31:36.659 --> 01:31:38.410
Look. I didn't know about Barnes.

1242
01:31:38.619 --> 01:31:39.995
ROGERS: Even if you had.
would you have told me?

1243
01:31:40.704 --> 01:31:43.415
Or would you have
compartmentalised that. too?

1244
01:31:43.624 --> 01:31:46.418
S.H.I.E.L.D.. HYDRA.

1245
01:31:46.627 --> 01:31:47.920
it all goes.

1246
01:31:48.420 --> 01:31:49.630
HILL: He's right.

1247
01:31:55.427 --> 01:31:56.470
WILSON: Don't look at me.

1248
01:31:56.679 --> 01:31:58.555
I do what he does. just slower.

1249
01:32:02.267 --> 01:32:03.936
Well...

1250
01:32:06.313 --> 01:32:07.856
(SIGHS)

1251
01:32:10.192 --> 01:32:12.611
It looks like you're giving
the orders now. Captain.

1252
01:32:24.248 --> 01:32:25.708
BUCKY: <i>We looked for you. after.</i>

1253
01:32:25.791 --> 01:32:26.917
(CHURCH BELL TOLLING)

1254
01:32:27.000 --> 01:32:29.002
<i>My folks wanted to give you
a ride to the cemetery.</i>

1255
01:32:29.211 --> 01:32:32.798
I know. I'm sorry.
I just kind of wanted to be alone.

1256
01:32:33.924 --> 01:32:35.300
How was it?

1257
01:32:35.801 --> 01:32:37.261
It was okay.

1258
01:32:37.720 --> 01:32:39.638
She's next to Dad.

1259
01:32:41.140 --> 01:32:42.391
I was gonna ask...

1260
01:32:42.808 --> 01:32:44.268
I know what you're gonna say. Buck.
I just...

1261
01:32:45.436 --> 01:32:46.937
BUCKY: We can put the
couch cushions on the floor

1262
01:32:47.146 --> 01:32:48.647
like when we were kids.

1263
01:32:49.314 --> 01:32:51.817
It'll be fun.
All you got to do is shine my shoes.

1264
01:32:52.234 --> 01:32:53.902
maybe take out the trash.

1265
01:32:58.949 --> 01:33:00.367
Come on.

1266
01:33:03.412 --> 01:33:06.832
Thank you. Buck.
but I can get by on my own.

1267
01:33:07.624 --> 01:33:11.420
The thing is. you don't have to.

1268
01:33:14.757 --> 01:33:16.341
I'm with you to the end of the line. pal.

1269
01:33:17.468 --> 01:33:18.677
(SIGHS)

1270
01:33:19.678 --> 01:33:21.013
He's gonna be there. you know.

1271
01:33:21.096 --> 01:33:22.139
I know.

1272
01:33:23.015 --> 01:33:26.351
Look. whoever he used to be
and the guy he is now.

1273
01:33:27.019 --> 01:33:29.188
I don't think he's the kind you save.

1274
01:33:29.396 --> 01:33:30.856
He's the kind you stop.

1275
01:33:33.525 --> 01:33:35.110
I don't know if I can do that.

1276
01:33:35.444 --> 01:33:37.404
Well. he might not give you a choice.

1277
01:33:37.613 --> 01:33:39.072
He doesn't know you.

1278
01:33:39.782 --> 01:33:40.824
He will.

1279
01:33:43.619 --> 01:33:44.870
Gear up. It's time.

1280
01:33:47.539 --> 01:33:48.624
You gonna wear that?

1281
01:33:48.874 --> 01:33:52.252
No. If you're gonna fight a war.
you got to wear a uniform.

1282
01:34:00.177 --> 01:34:01.595
Oh. man.

1283
01:34:02.387 --> 01:34:04.473
I am so fired.

1284
01:34:29.373 --> 01:34:31.583
MAN ON PA:
<i>We are in final launch sequence.</i>

1285
01:34:33.252 --> 01:34:35.170
We are go on guidance.

1286
01:34:37.089 --> 01:34:39.216
WOMAN ON PA:
<i>All personnel to launch stations.</i>

1287
01:34:39.967 --> 01:34:41.134
PIERCE:And how was your flight?

1288
01:34:41.343 --> 01:34:42.386
HAWLEY: Lovely.

1289
01:34:42.469 --> 01:34:44.972
The ride from the airport. less so.

1290
01:34:45.097 --> 01:34:47.599
Sadly. S.H.I.E.L.D. can't
control everything.

1291
01:34:47.766 --> 01:34:49.685
Including Captain America.

1292
01:34:53.105 --> 01:34:55.691
This facility is biometrically controlled.

1293
01:34:55.899 --> 01:34:58.777
And these will give you
unrestricted access.

1294
01:35:02.739 --> 01:35:03.907
TECH 1 :
I've been parking there for two months.

1295
01:35:04.116 --> 01:35:05.701
TECH 2: But it's his spot.
TECH 1 : So where's he been?

1296
01:35:05.909 --> 01:35:07.160
TECH 2: I think Afghanistan.

1297
01:35:07.244 --> 01:35:09.246
Negative DT Six. The pattern is full.

1298
01:35:09.454 --> 01:35:10.747
Well. he could've said something.

1299
01:35:10.831 --> 01:35:12.332
- (HIGH-PITCHED FEEDBACK)
- ALL: Ahh!

1300
01:35:12.416 --> 01:35:13.709
Must be the dish.

1301
01:35:15.502 --> 01:35:17.129
I'll check it out.

1302
01:35:17.963 --> 01:35:20.966
MAN ON PA: <i>Triskelion command
request we clear the area for launch.</i>

1303
01:35:24.636 --> 01:35:25.596
Excuse us.

1304
01:35:25.679 --> 01:35:28.140
PIERCE: <i>I know the road
hasn't exactly been smooth.</i>

1305
01:35:28.640 --> 01:35:31.977
and some of you would have gladly
kicked me out of the car along the way.

1306
01:35:34.229 --> 01:35:35.188
Finally. we're here.

1307
01:35:35.939 --> 01:35:37.858
And the world should be grateful.

1308
01:35:38.817 --> 01:35:40.527
ROGERS ON PA:
<i>Attention all S.H.I.E.L.D. agents.</i>

1309
01:35:40.736 --> 01:35:42.487
<i>this is Steve Rogers.</i>

1310
01:35:44.281 --> 01:35:46.491
<i>You've heard a lot about me
over the last few days.</i>

1311
01:35:47.534 --> 01:35:49.786
<i>Some of you were even ordered
to hunt me down.</i>

1312
01:35:50.495 --> 01:35:53.373
But I think it's time you know the truth.

1313
01:35:56.501 --> 01:35:58.670
S.H.I.E.L.D. is not
what we thought it was.

1314
01:35:58.879 --> 01:36:00.589
It's been taken over by HYDRA.

1315
01:36:01.715 --> 01:36:03.383
<i>Alexander Pierce is their leader.</i>

1316
01:36:07.512 --> 01:36:09.848
<i>The S.T.R.I.K.E. and Insight crew
are HYDRA as well.</i>

1317
01:36:10.057 --> 01:36:11.099
<i>I don't know how many more.</i>

1318
01:36:12.392 --> 01:36:13.393
but I know they're in the building.

1319
01:36:15.187 --> 01:36:17.064
<i>They could be standing
right next to you.</i>

1320
01:36:18.649 --> 01:36:20.317
<i>They almost have what they want.</i>

1321
01:36:21.109 --> 01:36:23.195
<i>Absolute control.</i>

1322
01:36:23.695 --> 01:36:25.030
They shot Nick Fury.

1323
01:36:26.156 --> 01:36:27.282
<i>And it won't end there.</i>

1324
01:36:27.824 --> 01:36:30.035
If you launch those helicarriers today.

1325
01:36:30.202 --> 01:36:32.204
<i>HYDRA will be able to kill
anyone that stands in their way.</i>

1326
01:36:35.499 --> 01:36:36.875
<i>Unless we stop them.</i>

1327
01:36:40.879 --> 01:36:42.005
<i>I know I'm asking a lot.</i>

1328
01:36:43.924 --> 01:36:47.094
<i>But the price of freedom is high.
It always has been.</i>

1329
01:36:47.844 --> 01:36:49.721
And it's a price I'm willing to pay.

1330
01:36:52.099 --> 01:36:54.893
And if I'm the only one. then so be it.

1331
01:36:56.561 --> 01:36:58.313
But I'm willing to bet I'm not.

1332
01:37:03.068 --> 01:37:06.363
Did you write that down first.
or was it off the top of your head?

1333
01:37:06.863 --> 01:37:08.490
You smug son of a bitch.

1334
01:37:12.577 --> 01:37:13.620
Arrest him.

1335
01:37:16.498 --> 01:37:18.125
I guess I've got the floor.

1336
01:37:25.007 --> 01:37:27.926
Preempt the launch sequence.
Send those ships up now.

1337
01:37:32.305 --> 01:37:33.807
Is there a problem?

1338
01:37:33.890 --> 01:37:34.891
Um...

1339
01:37:38.854 --> 01:37:39.938
Is there a problem?

1340
01:37:40.105 --> 01:37:41.189
I'm sorry. sir.

1341
01:37:42.065 --> 01:37:43.775
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1342
01:37:49.906 --> 01:37:52.117
I'm not gonna launch those ships.

1343
01:37:54.828 --> 01:37:56.121
Captain's orders.

1344
01:37:56.329 --> 01:37:57.581
Move away from your station.

1345
01:37:57.956 --> 01:37:58.999
Like he said...

1346
01:37:59.166 --> 01:38:00.208
Hold it right there.

1347
01:38:00.292 --> 01:38:01.626
Put the gun down!

1348
01:38:01.793 --> 01:38:02.794
Captain's orders.

1349
01:38:05.213 --> 01:38:06.631
You picked the wrong side. Agent.

1350
01:38:08.467 --> 01:38:10.093
Depends on where you're standing.

1351
01:38:21.938 --> 01:38:23.315
- (GUN CLATTERS)
- (GASPS)

1352
01:38:24.191 --> 01:38:25.650
- (GROANS)
- (PEOPLE GASP)

1353
01:38:27.110 --> 01:38:29.154
(ALL GRUNTING)

1354
01:38:54.471 --> 01:38:55.931
S.H.I.E.L.D. AGENT:
Close the bay door!

1355
01:38:56.139 --> 01:38:57.349
Close the bay door now!

1356
01:38:57.849 --> 01:38:58.809
Close the bay door!

1357
01:39:18.662 --> 01:39:19.871
They're initiating launch.

1358
01:39:40.100 --> 01:39:42.686
Hey. Cap. how do we know
the good guys from the bad guys?

1359
01:39:42.894 --> 01:39:44.354
If they're shooting at you. they're bad.

1360
01:40:01.872 --> 01:40:03.206
(GROANING)

1361
01:40:17.721 --> 01:40:18.722
Hey. Cap.

1362
01:40:18.930 --> 01:40:20.932
I found those bad guys
you were talking about.

1363
01:40:21.016 --> 01:40:22.017
You okay?

1364
01:40:24.144 --> 01:40:25.687
I'm not dead yet.

1365
01:40:32.652 --> 01:40:34.404
PIERCE: Let me ask you a question.

1366
01:40:36.907 --> 01:40:40.035
What if Pakistan marched
into Mumbai tomorrow

1367
01:40:41.328 --> 01:40:43.455
and you knew that they were
going to drag your daughters

1368
01:40:43.663 --> 01:40:46.458
into a soccer stadium for execution.

1369
01:40:48.877 --> 01:40:52.214
and you could just stop it.
with a flick of the switch.

1370
01:40:52.422 --> 01:40:53.590
Wouldn't you?

1371
01:40:53.798 --> 01:40:55.425
Wouldn't you all?

1372
01:40:57.302 --> 01:40:58.803
Not if it was your switch.

1373
01:40:59.763 --> 01:41:01.348
(GLASS SHATTERS)

1374
01:41:02.015 --> 01:41:03.141
(CHUCKLES)

1375
01:41:08.230 --> 01:41:09.731
(ALL GRUNTING)

1376
01:41:23.328 --> 01:41:24.537
I'm sorry.

1377
01:41:30.961 --> 01:41:32.504
Did I step on your moment?

1378
01:41:34.089 --> 01:41:36.341
Satellites in range at 3.000 feet.

1379
01:41:37.300 --> 01:41:38.468
Falcon. status?

1380
01:41:38.718 --> 01:41:39.886
Engaging.

1381
01:42:03.994 --> 01:42:05.287
All right. Cap. I'm in.

1382
01:42:07.664 --> 01:42:08.707
Oh. shit.

1383
01:42:32.564 --> 01:42:34.065
(ALL GRUNTING)

1384
01:42:39.237 --> 01:42:40.697
HILL: <i>Eight minutes. Cap.</i>

1385
01:42:41.197 --> 01:42:42.574
Working on it.

1386
01:42:50.915 --> 01:42:51.958
What are you doing?

1387
01:42:52.042 --> 01:42:53.626
She's disabling security protocols

1388
01:42:53.710 --> 01:42:55.462
and dumping all the secrets
onto the Internet.

1389
01:42:55.670 --> 01:42:57.255
- Including HYDRA's.
- And S.H.I.E.L.D.'s.

1390
01:42:58.590 --> 01:42:59.674
If you do this.

1391
01:42:59.924 --> 01:43:01.593
none of your past is
gonna remain hidden.

1392
01:43:04.679 --> 01:43:07.182
Are you sure you're ready
for the world to see you

1393
01:43:07.390 --> 01:43:08.933
as you really are?

1394
01:43:09.684 --> 01:43:11.102
Are you?

1395
01:43:27.369 --> 01:43:28.411
Alpha lock.

1396
01:43:30.538 --> 01:43:31.831
Falcon. where are you now?

1397
01:43:31.998 --> 01:43:32.916
I had to take a detour.

1398
01:44:00.360 --> 01:44:01.403
(GRUNTS)

1399
01:44:03.822 --> 01:44:04.823
Whoo!

1400
01:44:05.532 --> 01:44:07.117
Oh. yeah!

1401
01:44:13.123 --> 01:44:14.165
I'm in.

1402
01:44:17.794 --> 01:44:19.629
Bravo lock.

1403
01:44:21.423 --> 01:44:22.715
Two down. one to go.

1404
01:44:25.009 --> 01:44:26.511
LEAD PILOT:
All S.H.I.E.L.D. pilots. scramble.

1405
01:44:27.387 --> 01:44:30.014
We're the only air support
Captain Rogers has got.

1406
01:44:43.111 --> 01:44:44.362
(GROANS)

1407
01:45:12.474 --> 01:45:15.143
Disabling the encryption
is an executive order.

1408
01:45:15.351 --> 01:45:17.020
It takes two Alpha Level members.

1409
01:45:17.228 --> 01:45:19.189
Don't worry. Company's coming.

1410
01:45:19.272 --> 01:45:20.732
(HELICOPTER APPROACHING)

1411
01:45:42.795 --> 01:45:43.922
Did you get my flowers?

1412
01:45:46.633 --> 01:45:48.301
- PIERCE: I'm glad you're here. Nick.
- Really?

1413
01:45:50.261 --> 01:45:52.138
Because I thought you had me killed.

1414
01:45:52.347 --> 01:45:53.806
You know how the game works.

1415
01:45:54.891 --> 01:45:56.601
So why make me head of S.H.I.E.L.D.?

1416
01:45:56.684 --> 01:45:57.977
Because you were the best.

1417
01:45:58.144 --> 01:45:59.604
and the most ruthless person
I ever met.

1418
01:45:59.938 --> 01:46:02.148
I did what I did to protect people.

1419
01:46:03.066 --> 01:46:05.026
Our enemies are your enemies. Nick.

1420
01:46:05.944 --> 01:46:08.279
Disorder. War.

1421
01:46:09.280 --> 01:46:11.616
It's just a matter of time
before a dirty bomb goes off in Moscow.

1422
01:46:11.783 --> 01:46:13.952
or an EMP fries Chicago.

1423
01:46:15.537 --> 01:46:16.955
Diplomacy?

1424
01:46:17.121 --> 01:46:19.457
A holding action. Nick. A band-aid.

1425
01:46:20.375 --> 01:46:23.294
And you know where
I learned that. Bogota.

1426
01:46:25.046 --> 01:46:27.757
You didn't ask.
You just did what had to be done.

1427
01:46:28.967 --> 01:46:33.263
I can bring order to the lives
of seven billion people

1428
01:46:33.972 --> 01:46:35.598
by sacrificing 20 million.

1429
01:46:37.141 --> 01:46:39.102
It's the next step. Nick.

1430
01:46:39.310 --> 01:46:40.436
If you have the courage to take it.

1431
01:46:40.645 --> 01:46:42.730
No. I have the courage not to.

1432
01:46:47.235 --> 01:46:49.112
S.H.I.E.L.D. COMPUTER:
<i>Retinal scanner active.</i>

1433
01:46:49.195 --> 01:46:50.488
(CHUCKLES)

1434
01:46:50.613 --> 01:46:52.991
You don't think we've wiped
your clearance from the system?

1435
01:46:53.157 --> 01:46:55.118
I know you erased my password.

1436
01:46:55.326 --> 01:46:57.245
Probably deleted my retinal scan.

1437
01:46:57.787 --> 01:47:00.623
But if you want to stay ahead
of me. Mr Secretary.

1438
01:47:04.627 --> 01:47:07.589
you need to keep both eyes open.

1439
01:47:12.010 --> 01:47:13.511
COMPUTER: <i>Alpha level confirmed.</i>

1440
01:47:14.012 --> 01:47:15.847
<i>Encryption code accepted.</i>

1441
01:47:16.014 --> 01:47:17.181
<i>Safeguards removed.</i>

1442
01:47:17.557 --> 01:47:20.560
Charlie carrier is
45 degrees off the port bow.

1443
01:47:24.230 --> 01:47:25.690
(HYDRA SOLDIERS GROANING)

1444
01:47:26.274 --> 01:47:27.358
Six minutes.

1445
01:47:27.525 --> 01:47:29.986
Hey. Sam. gonna need a ride.

1446
01:47:30.862 --> 01:47:32.530
Roger. Let me know when you're ready.

1447
01:47:35.158 --> 01:47:36.367
I just did!

1448
01:47:44.709 --> 01:47:46.294
(GROANS)

1449
01:47:54.135 --> 01:47:56.054
You know. you're a lot heavier
than you look.

1450
01:47:56.220 --> 01:47:57.347
I had a big breakfast.

1451
01:47:59.974 --> 01:48:01.267
Steve!

1452
01:48:03.102 --> 01:48:04.520
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1453
01:48:27.669 --> 01:48:28.920
(YELLING)

1454
01:48:31.756 --> 01:48:33.132
WILSON: <i>Cap! Cap. come in.
Are you okay?</i>

1455
01:48:33.716 --> 01:48:35.009
Yeah. I'm here.

1456
01:48:35.551 --> 01:48:36.594
I'm still on the helicarrier.

1457
01:48:37.637 --> 01:48:39.263
- Where are you?
- <i>I'm grounded.</i>

1458
01:48:39.889 --> 01:48:42.225
The suit's down. Sorry. Cap.

1459
01:48:43.059 --> 01:48:44.936
Don't worry. I got it.

1460
01:48:45.853 --> 01:48:46.854
(ALARM BLARING)

1461
01:48:46.938 --> 01:48:48.439
WOMAN: (ON PA)
<i>Emergency evacuation alert.</i>

1462
01:48:48.648 --> 01:48:51.609
<i>All personnel. proceed to
designated safety zones.</i>

1463
01:48:53.194 --> 01:48:55.071
S.H.I.E.L.D. AGENT: All S.H.I.E.L.D.
agents regroup at Rally Point Delta.

1464
01:48:55.154 --> 01:48:57.281
- (YELLS)
- (ALL GRUNTING)

1465
01:49:00.785 --> 01:49:02.912
DISPATCH: (ON RADIO)
<i>Sir. the Council's been breached.</i>

1466
01:49:03.246 --> 01:49:05.623
- Repeat. Dispatch.
- <i>Black Widow's up there.</i>

1467
01:49:05.832 --> 01:49:07.166
Headed up.

1468
01:49:09.377 --> 01:49:10.628
- Falcon?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

1469
01:49:10.753 --> 01:49:11.713
Rumlow's headed for the Council.

1470
01:49:11.796 --> 01:49:12.797
I'm on it.

1471
01:49:24.392 --> 01:49:25.435
People are gonna die. Buck.

1472
01:49:27.562 --> 01:49:29.021
I can't let that happen.

1473
01:49:37.488 --> 01:49:38.823
Please don't make me do this.

1474
01:49:57.467 --> 01:49:59.343
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1475
01:50:49.060 --> 01:50:50.061
Done.

1476
01:50:51.062 --> 01:50:52.063
And it's trending.

1477
01:50:56.609 --> 01:50:57.944
(GROANING)

1478
01:50:59.737 --> 01:51:01.572
Unless you want a two-inch
hole in your sternum.

1479
01:51:01.656 --> 01:51:02.740
I'd put that gun down.

1480
01:51:05.451 --> 01:51:07.411
That was armed the moment
you pinned it on.

1481
01:51:22.760 --> 01:51:23.970
(GROANS)

1482
01:51:26.264 --> 01:51:27.265
Ahhh!

1483
01:51:41.237 --> 01:51:42.321
Drop it!

1484
01:51:42.947 --> 01:51:43.948
Drop it!

1485
01:51:44.115 --> 01:51:45.408
(SCREAMS)

1486
01:52:04.468 --> 01:52:07.722
I'm on 41. headed toward
the southwest stairwell.

1487
01:52:10.308 --> 01:52:12.643
(GROANING)

1488
01:52:14.437 --> 01:52:16.022
This is gonna hurt.

1489
01:52:17.315 --> 01:52:20.401
There are no prisoners with HYDRA.
Just order.

1490
01:52:20.610 --> 01:52:22.820
And order only comes through pain.

1491
01:52:24.238 --> 01:52:26.616
- You ready for yours?
- Man. shut the hell up.

1492
01:52:28.409 --> 01:52:29.744
Lieutenant. how much longer?

1493
01:52:29.827 --> 01:52:31.913
CHARLIE XO: (ON RADIO)
<i>65 seconds to satellite link.</i>

1494
01:52:31.996 --> 01:52:34.999
Targeting grid engaged.
Lowering weapons array now.

1495
01:52:39.003 --> 01:52:40.087
One minute.

1496
01:52:44.175 --> 01:52:45.843
- (GUNSHOT)
- (GROANS)

1497
01:52:59.982 --> 01:53:01.525
HILL: (ON RADIO) <i>30 seconds. Cap.</i>

1498
01:53:03.152 --> 01:53:04.695
Stand by. (GROANS)

1499
01:53:07.365 --> 01:53:08.991
Charlie... (GROANS)

1500
01:53:11.702 --> 01:53:13.120
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1501
01:53:18.292 --> 01:53:19.961
CHARLIE WEAPONS TECH:
(ON RADIO) <i>We've reached 3.000 feet.</i>

1502
01:53:20.586 --> 01:53:21.587
Sat link coming online now.

1503
01:53:24.131 --> 01:53:25.216
Deploy algorithm.

1504
01:53:26.884 --> 01:53:28.010
CHARLIE WEAPONS TECH:
Algorithm deployed.

1505
01:53:29.261 --> 01:53:30.721
PIERCE: (ON RADIO)
<i>We are go to target.</i>

1506
01:53:49.782 --> 01:53:51.158
CHARLIE WEAPONS TECH:
<i>Target saturation reached.</i>

1507
01:53:51.575 --> 01:53:52.576
All targets assigned.

1508
01:53:52.660 --> 01:53:53.661
Fire when ready.

1509
01:53:56.163 --> 01:53:57.373
Firing in...

1510
01:53:57.540 --> 01:53:58.582
<i>Three.</i>

1511
01:53:58.874 --> 01:53:59.875
two...

1512
01:53:59.959 --> 01:54:01.002
(GRUNTS)

1513
01:54:01.085 --> 01:54:02.420
One.

1514
01:54:05.089 --> 01:54:06.132
(PANTS) Charlie lock.

1515
01:54:06.590 --> 01:54:07.591
Where are the targets?

1516
01:54:09.093 --> 01:54:10.094
Where are the targets?

1517
01:54:10.720 --> 01:54:11.929
Okay. Cap. get out of there.

1518
01:54:29.363 --> 01:54:30.364
Fire now.

1519
01:54:31.449 --> 01:54:32.700
- But. Steve...
- Do it!

1520
01:54:33.451 --> 01:54:34.618
<i>Do it now!</i>

1521
01:54:57.850 --> 01:54:59.226
(WINTER SOLDIER SCREAMING)

1522
01:55:05.149 --> 01:55:06.150
What a waste.

1523
01:55:06.317 --> 01:55:09.528
ROMANOFF: So. you still on the fence
about Rogers' chances?

1524
01:55:09.737 --> 01:55:12.782
Time to go. Councilwoman. This way.
Come on.

1525
01:55:13.282 --> 01:55:14.784
You're going to fly me out of here.

1526
01:55:14.992 --> 01:55:18.162
You know. there was a time
I would've taken a bullet for you.

1527
01:55:18.370 --> 01:55:19.663
You already did.

1528
01:55:19.830 --> 01:55:21.791
- You will again. when it's useful.
- (GROANING)

1529
01:55:35.137 --> 01:55:36.263
Romanoff.

1530
01:55:37.014 --> 01:55:38.099
Natasha.

1531
01:55:40.142 --> 01:55:41.936
Natasha! Come on!

1532
01:55:46.315 --> 01:55:47.566
Ow.

1533
01:55:48.984 --> 01:55:50.528
Those really do sting.

1534
01:56:23.561 --> 01:56:24.979
(WEAKLY) Hail HYDRA.

1535
01:56:57.845 --> 01:56:59.221
(GRUNTING)

1536
01:57:13.194 --> 01:57:14.737
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1537
01:57:16.322 --> 01:57:17.573
(GROANS)

1538
01:57:20.451 --> 01:57:21.911
You're out of your depth. kid.

1539
01:57:25.623 --> 01:57:27.124
Son of a bitch!

1540
01:57:39.261 --> 01:57:40.846
Please tell me you got
that chopper in the air!

1541
01:57:41.639 --> 01:57:42.765
ROMANOFF: (ON RADIO)
<i>Sam. where are you?</i>

1542
01:57:43.641 --> 01:57:45.476
41st floor! Northwest corner!

1543
01:57:45.684 --> 01:57:47.228
We're on it! Stay where you are!

1544
01:57:47.436 --> 01:57:48.520
Not an option!

1545
01:58:03.327 --> 01:58:05.496
41st floor! 41st!

1546
01:58:05.829 --> 01:58:09.166
It's not like they put the floor numbers
on the outside of the building.

1547
01:58:10.542 --> 01:58:13.045
Hill! Where's Steve?
You got a location on Rogers?

1548
01:58:17.049 --> 01:58:18.759
(STRAINING)

1549
01:58:20.511 --> 01:58:21.762
(GRUNTS)

1550
01:58:29.520 --> 01:58:30.604
You know me.

1551
01:58:32.356 --> 01:58:33.691
No. I don't!

1552
01:58:40.990 --> 01:58:42.241
(PANTING)

1553
01:58:43.200 --> 01:58:44.535
Bucky.

1554
01:58:46.036 --> 01:58:47.496
You've known me your whole life.

1555
01:58:55.045 --> 01:58:58.966
Your name is James Buchanan Barnes.

1556
01:58:59.174 --> 01:59:00.384
Shut up!

1557
01:59:09.101 --> 01:59:10.561
I'm not gonna fight you.

1558
01:59:14.565 --> 01:59:15.899
You're my friend.

1559
01:59:19.903 --> 01:59:21.405
- (ROARS)
- (GRUNTS)

1560
01:59:22.906 --> 01:59:24.283
You're my mission.

1561
01:59:24.408 --> 01:59:25.743
(GRUNTING)

1562
01:59:26.577 --> 01:59:28.579
You're my mission!

1563
01:59:31.915 --> 01:59:32.916
Then finish it.

1564
01:59:36.420 --> 01:59:38.589
Because I'm with you
to the end of the line.

1565
02:01:26.738 --> 02:01:28.490
(R&B MUSIC PLAYING)

1566
02:01:50.262 --> 02:01:51.597
On your left.

1567
02:01:57.227 --> 02:01:59.271
(R&B MUSIC CONTINUES PLAYING)

1568
02:02:17.498 --> 02:02:19.500
(INAUDIBLE)

1569
02:02:42.606 --> 02:02:44.983
FEMALE BAILIFF: <i>Do you solemnly
swear to tell the truth. the whole truth.</i>

1570
02:02:45.192 --> 02:02:46.276
<i>and nothing but the truth?</i>

1571
02:02:46.485 --> 02:02:47.903
ROMANOFF: <i>I do.</i>

1572
02:02:49.905 --> 02:02:51.615
COMMITTEE MEMBER: <i>Why haven't
we yet heard from Captain Rogers?</i>

1573
02:02:51.782 --> 02:02:53.158
(CAMERAS CLICKING)

1574
02:02:54.326 --> 02:02:56.245
I don't know what there is
left for him to say.

1575
02:02:56.453 --> 02:02:58.288
I think the wreck in
the middle of the Potomac

1576
02:02:58.497 --> 02:02:59.665
made his point fairly eloquently.

1577
02:02:59.873 --> 02:03:00.832
COMMITTEE MEMBER:
Well. he could explain how

1578
02:03:01.041 --> 02:03:03.627
this country is expected to maintain
its national security

1579
02:03:03.794 --> 02:03:07.923
now that he and you have laid waste
to our intelligence apparatus.

1580
02:03:08.340 --> 02:03:10.300
HYDRA was selling you lies.
not intelligence.

1581
02:03:10.467 --> 02:03:13.345
Many of which you seemed to have had
a personal hand in telling.

1582
02:03:13.554 --> 02:03:14.805
Agent. you should know

1583
02:03:14.972 --> 02:03:16.640
that there are some on this committee

1584
02:03:16.848 --> 02:03:18.976
who feel. given your service record.

1585
02:03:19.142 --> 02:03:20.894
both for this country and against it.

1586
02:03:21.645 --> 02:03:23.397
that you belong in a penitentiary.

1587
02:03:23.605 --> 02:03:25.566
Not mouthing off on Capitol Hill.

1588
02:03:27.484 --> 02:03:29.069
You're not going to put me in a prison.

1589
02:03:30.070 --> 02:03:33.991
You're not going to put any of us
in a prison. You know why?

1590
02:03:35.450 --> 02:03:36.827
Do enlighten us.

1591
02:03:37.119 --> 02:03:38.453
Because you need us.

1592
02:03:39.580 --> 02:03:41.832
<i>Yes. the world is a vulnerable place.</i>

1593
02:03:42.040 --> 02:03:44.209
<i>and yes. we help make it that way.</i>

1594
02:03:44.751 --> 02:03:47.504
<i>But we're also the ones
best qualified to defend it.</i>

1595
02:03:49.172 --> 02:03:51.133
So. if you want to arrest me. arrest me.

1596
02:03:52.175 --> 02:03:53.844
You'll know where to find me.

1597
02:04:29.338 --> 02:04:32.174
So. you've experienced
this sort of thing before.

1598
02:04:32.674 --> 02:04:34.217
You get used to it.

1599
02:04:36.928 --> 02:04:39.097
We've been data mining HYDRA's files.

1600
02:04:39.306 --> 02:04:41.433
Looks like a lot of rats
didn't go down with the ship.

1601
02:04:43.018 --> 02:04:44.353
I'm headed to Europe tonight.

1602
02:04:45.312 --> 02:04:46.563
Wanted to ask if you'd come.

1603
02:04:47.731 --> 02:04:49.358
There's something I got to do first.

1604
02:04:50.275 --> 02:04:52.819
How about you. Wilson?
Could use a man with your abilities.

1605
02:04:53.862 --> 02:04:55.572
I'm more of a soldier than a spy.

1606
02:04:56.698 --> 02:04:58.450
All right. then.

1607
02:05:03.080 --> 02:05:07.292
Anybody asks for me.
tell them they can find me. right here.

1608
02:05:09.086 --> 02:05:10.671
You should be honoured.
That's about as close as he gets

1609
02:05:10.879 --> 02:05:12.506
to saying thank you.

1610
02:05:13.674 --> 02:05:14.758
Not going with him?

1611
02:05:15.258 --> 02:05:16.510
No.

1612
02:05:16.718 --> 02:05:18.720
- Not staying here.
- Nah.

1613
02:05:19.554 --> 02:05:21.598
I blew all my covers.
I got to go figure out a new one.

1614
02:05:21.932 --> 02:05:22.933
That might take a while.

1615
02:05:23.433 --> 02:05:25.060
I'm counting on it.

1616
02:05:27.270 --> 02:05:28.397
That thing you asked for.

1617
02:05:28.772 --> 02:05:31.066
I called in a few favours from Kiev.

1618
02:05:34.027 --> 02:05:36.780
Will you do me a favour? Call that nurse.

1619
02:05:37.197 --> 02:05:38.407
She's not a nurse.

1620
02:05:38.615 --> 02:05:40.450
And you're not a S.H.I.E.L.D. agent.

1621
02:05:41.368 --> 02:05:43.453
- What was her name again?
- Sharon.

1622
02:05:44.204 --> 02:05:45.205
She's nice.

1623
02:05:57.676 --> 02:05:59.428
Be careful. Steve.

1624
02:06:00.262 --> 02:06:02.013
You might not want to
pull on that thread.

1625
02:06:13.567 --> 02:06:15.318
You're going after him.

1626
02:06:15.736 --> 02:06:16.987
You don't have to come with me.

1627
02:06:17.154 --> 02:06:18.238
I know.

1628
02:06:20.198 --> 02:06:21.366
When do we start?

1629
02:08:20.777 --> 02:08:24.406
It's over. Fury has released
everything to the public.

1630
02:08:25.115 --> 02:08:26.449
Everything he knows about.

1631
02:08:27.033 --> 02:08:28.869
<i>Herr</i> Strucker. if they get
word of our work here.

1632
02:08:29.077 --> 02:08:30.871
if they find out we serve HYDRA...

1633
02:08:31.079 --> 02:08:32.789
HYDRA. S.H.I.E.L.D.

1634
02:08:33.790 --> 02:08:36.626
Two sides of a coin
that's no longer currency.

1635
02:08:40.463 --> 02:08:41.965
What we have

1636
02:08:44.009 --> 02:08:46.636
is worth more than
any of them ever knew.

1637
02:08:49.264 --> 02:08:52.976
We've only scratched
the surface and already.

1638
02:08:55.770 --> 02:08:59.608
there are other facilities doing
HYDRA's good work around the world.

1639
02:09:00.775 --> 02:09:04.195
We'll feed them to Captain America
and his colourful friends.

1640
02:09:04.404 --> 02:09:06.239
and keep them off our scent.

1641
02:09:06.448 --> 02:09:08.700
What about the volunteers?

1642
02:09:08.909 --> 02:09:10.452
The dead will be buried so deep

1643
02:09:10.660 --> 02:09:12.787
their own ghosts won't
be able to find them.

1644
02:09:14.873 --> 02:09:16.124
And the survivors?

1645
02:09:18.251 --> 02:09:19.753
The twins.

1646
02:09:23.340 --> 02:09:26.426
Sooner or later. they will meet the twins.

1647
02:09:28.637 --> 02:09:30.555
It's not a world of spies any more.

1648
02:09:30.764 --> 02:09:32.724
Not even a world of heroes.

1649
02:09:33.725 --> 02:09:36.436
This is the age of miracles. Doctor.

1650
02:09:38.313 --> 02:09:40.607
There's nothing more horrifying

1651
02:09:41.441 --> 02:09:42.567
than a miracle.
